ccurrences of \"L2 node(s)\" that need to change to \"L2 app(s)\"\n- 09:45 AM — Heartbeat: identified 15 places to change, awaiting order (combine first or terminology fix first)\n- 09:54 AM — Allan asked: since L2 is \"apps\", should L1 be \"nodes\" to match? Ledger is function, not entity\n- 09:55 AM — Proposed: rename \"Ledger Registry\" → \"Node Registry\" for symmetry (L1 nodes, L2 apps)\n- 09:56 AM — Allan approved: change all L1 and L2 naming\n- 09:57 AM — Changed \"Ledger Registry\" → \"Node Registry\" (4 places: Ch5 title, 5.1 title, overview, cross-registry ops)\n- 09:58 AM — Changed \"L2 node(s)\" → \"L2 app(s)\" (12 places throughout whitepaper)\n- 10:00 AM — Heartbeat: completed 16 naming changes. Ready to combine Ch5+Ch6 into \"Registry Operations\"\n- 10:15 AM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's confirmation to combine Ch5+Ch6 into \"Registry Operations\"\n- 10:16 AM — Allan: 3.2 and 3.3 title should change too\n- 10:17 AM — Asked Allan what 3.2 (Identity) and 3.3 (Trust Model) should change to\n- 10:30 AM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's clarification on 3.2 and 3.3 title changes\n- 10:32 AM — Allan asked which file I'm reading — confirmed WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md\n- 10:41 AM — Allan asked if 3.1 titles are correct: Layer 1 (Registry), Layer 2 (Application)\n- 10:42 AM — Found inconsistency: \"Application nodes\" should be \"Applications\" (L2 are apps, not nodes)\n- 10:43 AM — Allan asked: should it be \"Layer 1 (Nodes)\" to match entity naming?\n- 10:44 AM — Changed \"Layer 1 (Registry)\" → \"Layer 1 (Nodes)\" for consistency\n- 10:45 AM — Heartbeat: fixed 3.1 titles to be entity-based (Nodes, Application), ready for Ch5+Ch6 combine\n- 10:46 AM — Allan: L2 graph legend shows \"App nodes\", Layer 1 title shows \"(Registry)\" — both need changing\n- 10:49 AM — Fixed topology-l2-v13.svg, but Allan pointed to v14 (latest version)\n- 10:52 AM — Found and fixed topology-l2-v14.svg: \"App nodes\" → \"Applications\", \"(Registry)\" → \"(Nodes)\"\n- 10:56 AM — Allan