{"type":"message","id":"be0ace8a","parentId":"ff9f836f","timestamp":"2026-03-11T01:30:28.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Discussing app registration with Allan — questioning whether apps need to register on a decentralized network."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a681b7c588a34bcaa6a1e581","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 07:15 AM — Heartbeat: Ch5 draft complete, awaiting Allan's review\n- 07:30 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n- 09:19 AM — Allan: morning\n- 09:21 AM — Allan asked to see 5.2\n- 09:25 AM — Allan: don't write yet, discuss first. Asked me to read this morning's conversation about app registration\n- 09:28 AM — Found conversation: Allan explained apps register like users (generate key, register with L1). Purpose: authentication, authorization, accountability\n- 09:29 AM — Asked Allan: why do apps need to register on a decentralized network? Is it for rate limiting tiers, or can anyone query L1 without registration?\n- 09:30 AM — Heartbeat: discussing app registration purpose with Allan","oldText":"- 07:15 AM — Heartbeat: Ch5 draft complete, awaiting Allan's review\n- 07:30 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":68007,"output":273,"cacheRead":6016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74296,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773192600469}}
