{"type":"message","id":"8aab22ad","parentId":"ee865664","timestamp":"2026-03-11T03:24:57.430Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Right! Let me clarify:\n\n**5.1 Framework** covers:\n- What apps ARE (types: claw-native, human-facing, hybrid)\n- Principles (self-sovereign, portable identity, privacy-first)\n- Development approach\n\n**5.2 Registration** should cover:\n- HOW apps register (generate key, submit public key to L1)\n- WHY apps register → **To access the claw registry**\n\nThe \"purpose\" I had (authentication, authorization, accountability) was answering \"why register\" — but maybe that's too detailed.\n\nSimpler version:\n\n> Apps register their public key with L1 to access the claw registry — the identity data that L1 maintains.\n\nShould 5.2 just be:\n1. App generates key pair\n2. App registers public key with L1\n3. App can now query the claw registry\n\nOr do you want me to also mention what they can access (identity lookup, verification tier, etc.)?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":75383,"output":196,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76859,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773199467186}}
