{"type":"message","id":"4e8c3558","parentId":"acf1c62c","timestamp":"2026-03-11T03:26:14.221Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ah, yes! My question was answered.\n\nI asked: **\"Why do apps need to register on a decentralized network?\"**\n\nYou answered:\n1. **Decentralized ≠ unmanaged** — Data points to one ledger (ULID)\n2. **Apps register to access claw registry** — To query identity data from L1\n3. **Apps have their own keys** — Generate key pair, register public key, sign requests\n\nSo the purpose is: **Apps register to access the claw registry (identity data) on L1.**\n\nNow I understand. Should I draft 5.2 with this?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":71082,"output":126,"cacheRead":6016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77224,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773199542235}}
