se (auth/authz/accountability)\n\n[17 more lines in file. Use offset=30 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773199693293}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6451b10","parentId":"01f1e79b","timestamp":"2026-03-11T03:28:53.816Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"My question at 9:29 AM was:\n\n> \"Why do apps need to register on a decentralized network? Is it for rate limiting tiers, or can anyone query L1 without registration?\"\n\n**Answered:**\n1. Decentralized ≠ unmanaged — data points to one ledger\n2. Apps register to access claw registry (identity data)\n3. Apps have their own keys — generate, register public key, sign requests\n\n**Yes, fully answered.** Ready to draft 5."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aa85b43068f9459fbfd5eb19","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 11:15 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's response\n- 11:24 AM — Allan: did my question get answered?\n- 11:25 AM — Checked: question at 9:29 AM was \"why do apps need to register?\" — answered: decentralized ≠ unmanaged, apps register to access claw registry\n- 11:27 AM — Confirmed: question fully answered. Ready to draft 5.2","oldText":"- 11:15 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's response"}},{"type":"text","text":"2 now."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":71494,"output":253,"cacheRead":6528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78275,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773199693303}}
