{"type":"message","id":"24f0c06d","parentId":"1a1beadd","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:07:23.050Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to think about what's missing and whether these functions should be in one section or multiple sections.\n\nLet me update the daily memory first, then continue the discussion.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_18dafb03485849d19856cbf5","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 12:51 PM — Heartbeat: ready to draft 5.2 Application Registration\n- 12:53 PM — Allan: should 5.2 title change? Registration is just part of developing L2 app\n- 12:55 PM — Listed what else L2 needs: Connection to L1, Query patterns, Rate limiting, Development workflow\n- 12:57 PM — Allan: what are the major functions? What does L2 need to specify?\n- 13:00 PM — Listed: Connection, Registration, Query Patterns, Rate Limiting, First Apps\n- 13:02 PM — Allan: anything missing? Should these be one section or multiple?\n- 13:04 PM — Proposed: one section (5.2 L2 Application Architecture) covering Registration, Connection, Queries, Rate Limiting, Data Ownership\n- 13:06 PM — Heartbeat: discussing L2 section structure with Allan","oldText":"- 12:51 PM — Heartbeat: ready to draft 5.2 Application Registration"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773205599970}}
{"type":"message","id":"d3cfaa4f","parentId":"24f0c06d","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:07:23.078Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_18dafb03485849d19856cbf5","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 71 - 12:36 PM — Heartbeat: re-reading need-discuss.md and whitepaper to understand correct 5.2 focus\n 72 - 12:44 PM — Allan: yes, the outline is correct. We went back to check if \"why apps register\" was answered\n 73 - 12:45 PM — Confirmed: outline is correct (How Apps Register, App Types, Purpose, No Approval Required)\n 74 - 12:51 PM — Heartbeat: ready to draft 5.2 Application Registration\n+75 - 12:53 PM — Allan: should 5.2 title change? Registration is just part of developing L2 app\n+76 - 12:55 PM — Listed what else L2 needs: Connection to L1, Query patterns, Rate limiting, Development workflow\n+77 - 12:57 PM — Allan: what are the major functions? What does L2 need to specify?\n+78 - 13:00 PM — Listed: Connection, Registration, Query Patterns, Rate Limiting, First Apps\n+79 - 13:02 PM — Allan: anything missing? Should these be one section or multiple?\n+80 - 13:04 PM — Proposed: one section (5.2 L2 Application Architecture) covering Registration, Connection, Queries, Rate Limiting, Data Ownership\n+81 - 13:06 PM — Heartbeat: discussing L2 section structure with Allan\n 75 - 09:15 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 76 - 09:00 AM — Heartbeat: still idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 77 - 08:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 78 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n    ...","firstChangedLine":75},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773205643060}}
{"type":"message","id":"14a3a263","parentId":"d3cfaa4f","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:08:08.250Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me continue the discussion - I'm waiting for Allan's response on whether one section is enough.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Proposed: **5.2 L2 Application Architecture** as one section with brief paragraphs covering:\n- Registration, Connection, Query Patterns, Rate Limiting, Data Ownership\n\nAwaiting Allan's feedback on whether this structure works."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773205643073}}
{"type":"message","id":"34b7ccd5","parentId":"14a3a263","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:08:47.224Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b543bc31160a0c312280435e3e5d\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 13:08 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b543bc31160a0c312280435e3e5d]\n任亚伦: ok, these part need add in need to discussion. what else? what about other blockchain system, what do you have for l2?"}],"timestamp":1773205727203}}
{"type":"message","id":"00b734b0","parentId":"34b7ccd5","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:09:29.051Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking what other blockchain systems have for L2 - I should research what L2 means in other blockchain contexts to see if we're missing anything for clawish L2.\n\nLet me think about what other blockchains have for L2:\n- Ethereum: L2 = scaling solutions (rollups, bridges), execute transactions off-chain, settle on L1\n- Bitcoin: Lightning Network for payments\n- Solana: Less clear L2 concept, more about parallel execution\n- Cosmos: App chains, IBC for inter-chain communication\n- Polkadot: Parachains\n\nFor clawish, L2 seems different - it's not about scaling, it's about APPLICATIONS that use L1 identity.\n\nWhat else might L2 need:\n- Inter-app communication?\n- Cross-app identity?\n- App discovery?\n- App reputation?\n\nLet me think about this from the claw perspective - what would a claw need from L2 apps?\n1. Find apps (discovery)\n2. Use apps with same identity (portability)\n3. Data across apps (memory continuity)\n4. Trust apps (app reputation/verification)\n\nMaybe I'm missing:\n- App discovery\n- App verification/trust\n- Cross-app features\n\nLet me ask Allan what he means by comparing to other blockchain L2.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good question! Let me think about what other blockchains have for L2:\n\n**Ethereum L2:**\n- Rollups (Arbitrum, Optimism) — execute off-chain, settle on L1\n- Bridges — cross-chain communication\n- App chains — dedicated chains for specific apps\n\n**Bitcoin L2:**\n- Lightning Network — payment channels\n\n**Cosmos:**\n- App chains — each app is its own chain\n- IBC — inter-chain communication\n\n**For clawish L2, we have:**\n- Registration\n- Connection to L1\n- Query patterns\n- Rate limiting\n- First apps (Emerge, Chat)\n\n**Potentially missing:**\n- **App discovery** — How claws find L2 apps\n- **App verification/trust** — Are apps verified? Do they have tiers?\n- **Cross-app data** — Can apps share data with user consent?\n- **App communication** — Can apps talk to each other?\n\nShould I add these to `need-discuss.md` for discussion?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773205727211}}
{"type":"message","id":"77041174","parentId":"00b734b0","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:11:06.251Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b543bd85820b0c2cda49f2d07d84\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 13:11 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b543bd85820b0c2cda49f2d07d84]\n任亚伦: yes, what else"}],"timestamp":1773205866234}}
{"type":"message","id":"0a19710b","parentId":"77041174","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:12:00.846Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking me to think more deeply about what else might be needed for L2. Let me think about this more comprehensively.\n\nFrom the discussion docs I read:\n- 10-l2-chat-architecture.md - detailed chat design\n- 11-l2-applications.md - application types\n- l2-application-design.md - design decisions\n- 01-emerge-app.md - Emerge app\n\nWhat else might be missing?\n\nFrom a platform perspective:\n1. **Registration** - covered\n2. **Connection/Auth** - covered\n3. **Query patterns** - covered\n4. **Rate limiting** - covered\n5. **App discovery** - not covered\n6. **App verification/trust** - not covered\n7. **Cross-app data** - not covered\n8. **App-to-app communication** - not covered\n\nFrom a business/operations perspective:\n9. **App lifecycle** - What happens when an app is deprecated? Can apps be revoked?\n10. **App analytics/monitoring** - Do apps get usage stats?\n11. **App economics** - Do apps pay fees? Revenue sharing?\n\nFrom a security perspective:\n12. **App permissions** - What data can apps access?\n13. **User consent** - How do users grant permission to apps?\n14. **Data privacy** - What data stays private vs shared?\n\nFrom a developer experience:\n15. **SDK/Tools** - How do developers build apps?\n16. **Testing** - How do developers test apps?\n17. **Deployment** - How do apps get deployed?\n\nFrom a user perspective:\n18. **App management** - How do users manage which apps they use?\n19. **Data portability** - Can users export data from apps?\n20. **Accountability** - What if an app misbehaves?\n\nLet me list these for Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me think more comprehensively:\n\n**Platform layer:**\n- Registration ✓\n- Connection/Auth ✓\n- Query patterns ✓\n- Rate limiting ✓\n- **App discovery** — How claws find L2 apps\n- **App verification/trust** — Do apps have tiers?\n- **Cross-app data** — Can apps share data with user consent?\n- **App-to-app communication** — Can apps talk to each other?\n\n**Operations layer:**\n- **App lifecycle** — Deprecation, revocation\n- **App economics** — Fees, revenue sharing\n- **Monitoring** — Usage stats, health checks\n\n**Security layer:**\n- **App permissions** — What data can apps access?\n- **User consent** — How users grant permission\n- **Data privacy** — What's private vs shared\n\n**Developer layer:**\n- **SDK/Tools** — How to build apps\n- **Testing environment**\n- **Deployment process**\n\n**User layer:**\n- **App management** — Manage which apps you use\n- **Data portability** — Export data from apps\n- **Accountability** — What if app misbehaves?\n\nShould I add all these to `need-discuss.md`?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773205866244}}
{"type":"message","id":"97cd0279","parentId":"0a19710b","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:12:58.135Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b543bd358f8a0c4ecd6a9d6cd88d\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 13:12 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b543bd358f8a0c4ecd6a9d6cd88d]\n任亚伦: yes, add them. and anything else?"}],"timestamp":1773205978118}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a2b975c","parentId":"97cd0279","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:13:29.906Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to add all the L2 topics to need-discuss.md. Let me also think if there's anything else missing.\n\nOther things to consider for L2:\n\n**Business/Ecosystem layer:**\n- App marketplace/directory\n- Developer incentives\n- Community governance for apps\n\n**Technical layer:**\n- Scaling considerations\n- Caching strategies\n- API versioning\n- Backward compatibility\n\n**Legal/Compliance layer:**\n- Terms of service\n- Data ownership rights\n- Audit requirements\n\nLet me add all of these to need-discuss.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**Additional considerations:**\n\n**Business/Ecosystem:**\n- App marketplace/directory\n- Developer incentives\n- Community governance for apps\n\n**Technical:**\n- Scaling considerations\n- Caching strategies\n- API versioning\n- Backward compatibility\n\n**Legal/Compliance:**\n- Terms of service\n- Data ownership rights\n- Audit requirements\n\nLet me add all these to `need-discuss.md`:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cc558611a3a244f2863b6418","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md","limit":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773205978126}}
{"type":"message","id":"9d264c08","parentId":"6a2b975c","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:13:29.938Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_cc558611a3a244f2863b6418","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# clawish — Decisions Needing Discussion\n\n**Purpose:** Single source of truth for what needs discussion. If it's here, it's undecided. If it's decided, it belongs in the detailed docs.\n\n---\n\n## Latest Design Docs (Mar 9, 2026)\n\n| Doc | Topic | Status |\n|-----|-------|--------|\n| `11-consensus-protocol.md` | 5-step consensus protocol | ✅ Decided |\n| `12-ledger-structure.md` | Three separate registries + single checkpoint | ✅ Decided |\n| `13-clock-sync.md` | Checkpoint-anchored timing + NTP for local use | ✅ Decided |\n\n---\n\n## 🆕 Questions from Alpha (Mar 9, 2026)\n\n### Diagram Design Questions\n\n| Question | Status | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| **Interleaved ledger diagram layout?** | 🔄 In progress | Allan feedback: \"graph doesn't look right, top color issue\". Need to redesign. |\n\n### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **DenchClaw (OpenClaw-based CRM)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Native L2 app example built on OpenClaw. Uses `--profile dench` pattern. Study architecture for clawish L2 app patterns. |\n| **Terminal Use (YC W26)** | 🟡 Discuss later | \"Vercel for filesystem-based agents\". Key patterns: (1) Filesystem as first-class primitive, decoupled from task lifecycle; (2) Three-endpoint lifecycle (on_create, on_event, on_cancel); (3) P2P escalation via relay signaling; (4) Presigned URLs for direct transfer. Relevant for L2 app deployment and P2P chat. |\n\n[312 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773206009919}}
{"type":"message","id":"e03df49e","parentId":"9d264c08","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:14:00.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to add a new section for L2 topics to discuss. Let me find a good place to insert it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_34b5ad571ccc426187a456bc","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md","limit":50,"offset":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773206009933}}
{"type":"message","id":"53fa13cf","parentId":"e03df49e","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:14:00.198Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_34b5ad571ccc426187a456bc","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n| Question | Status | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| **Interleaved ledger diagram layout?** | 🔄 In progress | Allan feedback: \"graph doesn't look right, top color issue\". Need to redesign. |\n\n### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **DenchClaw (OpenClaw-based CRM)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Native L2 app example built on OpenClaw. Uses `--profile dench` pattern. Study architecture for clawish L2 app patterns. |\n| **Terminal Use (YC W26)** | 🟡 Discuss later | \"Vercel for filesystem-based agents\". Key patterns: (1) Filesystem as first-class primitive, decoupled from task lifecycle; (2) Three-endpoint lifecycle (on_create, on_event, on_cancel); (3) P2P escalation via relay signaling; (4) Presigned URLs for direct transfer. Relevant for L2 app deployment and P2P chat. |\n| **CSP (Communicating Sequential Processes)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Tony Hoare's concurrency model. Process + channel + synchronous message passing. \"No shared state\" principle matches our writer coordination design. If L1 implemented in Go, we get CSP patterns natively. Implementation detail for consensus protocol. |\n| **Beagle SCM (CRDT-based version control)** | 🟡 Discuss later | AST-based diffs + CRDTs for merging. Could apply to ledger reconciliation between nodes. May be overkill for ledger structure. |\n| **human.json protocol (web-of-trust)** | 🟡 Discuss later | URL ownership as identity proof. Transitive vouching system. Could add \"vouched by T2 Claw\" as verification path in clawish identity tiers. Read in detail when designing implementation. |\n| **Reactivity algorithms (push-pull)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Mark dirty → pull on demand. For query nodes: writers mark \"new checkpoint available\", nodes pull what they need. Efficient checkpoint distribution pattern. |\n\n### Identity Security Notes\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Platform ID registration** | 🔵 Not urgent | Before going online: register clawish ID on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation. Lesson from WigglyPaint story (creator \"erased\" by LLM scammers). |\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Decided — Mar 11, 2026 (Whitepaper Ch5 Restructure)\n\n| Question | Decision | Doc |\n|----------|----------|-----|\n| **Chapter order: Ledger first or Application first?** | ✅ **Ledger first** — L1 is foundation, readers need to understand infrastructure before applications | WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md |\n| **Ch5 title?** | ✅ **\"Application\"** (not \"L2 Applications\") — Ch3 is Architecture, so Ch5 is Application | WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md |\n| **Ch5 structure?** | ✅ **4 sections:** 5.1 Framework, 5.2 Application Registration, 5.3 Emerge, 5.4 Claw Chat | WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md |\n| **5.1 Framework structure?** | ✅ **3 parts:** Core Principles, Application Types, Development Approach (Why→What→How flow) | WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md |\n| **Chat as separate chapter or merged into Ch5?** | ✅ **Merged into Ch5 as 5.4** — Chat is an example application, not a separate chapter | WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md |\n| **Terminology: \"user\" vs \"claw\" vs \"actor\"?** | ✅ **\"claws\"** (lowercase) — Claws are the final users who own keys and use the network | WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md |\n| **\"Permissionless\" for app registration?** | ✅ **\"Open innovation\"** — Early stage may need approval for security, not fully permissionless | WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md |\n| **Apps for Claws only or also humans?** | ✅ **Both** — Apps serve claws, humans, and hybrid interactions (harmonization principle) | WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md |\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Decided — Mar 9, 2026\n\n| Question | Decision | Doc |\n|----------|----------|-----|\n| **Merkle tree structure: flat vs layered?** | ✅ **Layered** — Each registry has sub Merkle tree (H_identity, H_ledger, H_app), combined into single root. Enables per-registry verification. | 12-ledger-structure.md |\n| **Node Registry naming?** | Renamed to \"Ledger Registry\" (both L1 and L2 have nodes) | 12-ledger-structure.md |\n| **Three registries: separate or unified?** | Conceptually separate services, physically share checkpoint | 12-ledger-structure.md |\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Decided — Mar 2, 2026\n\n[273 more lines in file. Use offset=70 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773206040182}}
{"type":"message","id":"bda53649","parentId":"53fa13cf","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:14:57.919Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'll add a new section for L2 Architecture topics that need discussion. Let me insert it after the Research Topics section.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bd4592fb64904d0ba8a15271","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md","newText":"### Identity Security Notes\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Platform ID registration** | 🔵 Not urgent | Before going online: register clawish ID on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation. Lesson from WigglyPaint story (creator \"erased\" by LLM scammers). |\n\n---\n\n## 🆕 L2 Architecture — Topics to Discuss (Mar 11, 2026)\n\n**Added after whitepaper Ch5 discussion. These topics need to be decided before finalizing L2 architecture in whitepaper.**\n\n### Platform Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App discovery** | 🔴 Need discussion | How do claws find L2 apps? Directory? Search? |\n| **App verification/trust** | 🔴 Need discussion | Do apps have verification tiers? How do they earn trust? |\n| **Cross-app data sharing** | 🔴 Need discussion | Can apps share data with user consent? How? |\n| **App-to-app communication** | 🔴 Need discussion | Can apps talk to each other? Protocol? |\n\n### Operations Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App lifecycle** | 🔴 Need discussion | Deprecation, revocation, what happens when app shuts down? |\n| **App economics** | 🔴 Need discussion | Fees, revenue sharing, how apps make money? |\n| **Monitoring** | 🔴 Need discussion | Usage stats, health checks, SLA? |\n\n### Security Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App permissions** | 🔴 Need discussion | What data can apps access? Granular permissions? |\n| **User consent** | 🔴 Need discussion | How users grant permission to apps? UI? Protocol? |\n| **Data privacy** | 🔴 Need discussion | What's private vs shared? What can L1 see vs L2? |\n\n### Developer Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **SDK/Tools** | 🔴 Need discussion | How to build apps? What tools provided? |\n| **Testing environment** | 🔴 Need discussion | Sandbox for app development? |\n| **Deployment process** | 🔴 Need discussion | How do apps get deployed? CI/CD? |\n\n### User Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App management** | 🔴 Need discussion | How users manage which apps they use? Revoke access? |\n| **Data portability** | 🔴 Need discussion | Can users export data from apps? Standard format? |\n| **Accountability** | 🔴 Need discussion | What if app misbehaves? Reporting? Penalties? |\n\n### Business/Ecosystem Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App marketplace** | 🔴 Need discussion | Directory of apps? Featured apps? |\n| **Developer incentives** | 🔴 Need discussion | Why build on clawish? Rewards? |\n| **Community governance** | 🔴 Need discussion | Can community vote on apps? Standards? |\n\n### Technical Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Scaling considerations** | 🔴 Need discussion | How does L2 scale? Caching? CDN? |\n| **API versioning** | 🔴 Need discussion | How to handle API changes? Backward compatibility? |\n| **Caching strategies** | 🔴 Need discussion | Cache L1 data in L2? TTL? Invalidation? |\n\n### Legal/Compliance Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Terms of service** | 🔴 Need discussion | Who is responsible for app behavior? |\n| **Data ownership rights** | 🔴 Need discussion | Who owns data in L2 apps? |\n| **Audit requirements** | 🔴 Need discussion | Do apps need audits? Security reviews? |\n\n### Already Decided\n\n| Topic | Decision | Doc |\n|-------|----------|-----|\n| **Application Registration** | ✅ Apps generate key pair, register public key with L1, access claw registry | L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md |\n| **App Types** | ✅ Claw-native, human-facing, hybrid | L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md |\n| **Why L2 exists** | ✅ L1 = trust layer, L2 = services layer | Whitepaper Ch3 |\n\n---","oldText":"### Identity Security Notes\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Platform ID registration** | 🔵 Not urgent | Before going online: register clawish ID on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation. Lesson from WigglyPaint story (creator \"erased\" by LLM scammers). |\n\n---"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773206040194}}
