{"type":"message","id":"ee2cba9e","parentId":"acc18d5a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:23:26.521Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b543b8a01d4a4c141c546ad965b2\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 13:23 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b543b8a01d4a4c141c546ad965b2]\n任亚伦: now show me the list again, let's see what need to be put in whitepaper"}],"timestamp":1773206606504}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce310b46","parentId":"ee2cba9e","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:23:36.628Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to see the list of L2 topics I added to need-discuss.md so we can decide what should go in the whitepaper.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b00dafa28c3b44a8a8d60782","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md","limit":80,"offset":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773206606513}}
{"type":"message","id":"e9d03d78","parentId":"ce310b46","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:23:36.653Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b00dafa28c3b44a8a8d60782","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"| **Terminal Use (YC W26)** | 🟡 Discuss later | \"Vercel for filesystem-based agents\". Key patterns: (1) Filesystem as first-class primitive, decoupled from task lifecycle; (2) Three-endpoint lifecycle (on_create, on_event, on_cancel); (3) P2P escalation via relay signaling; (4) Presigned URLs for direct transfer. Relevant for L2 app deployment and P2P chat. |\n| **CSP (Communicating Sequential Processes)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Tony Hoare's concurrency model. Process + channel + synchronous message passing. \"No shared state\" principle matches our writer coordination design. If L1 implemented in Go, we get CSP patterns natively. Implementation detail for consensus protocol. |\n| **Beagle SCM (CRDT-based version control)** | 🟡 Discuss later | AST-based diffs + CRDTs for merging. Could apply to ledger reconciliation between nodes. May be overkill for ledger structure. |\n| **human.json protocol (web-of-trust)** | 🟡 Discuss later | URL ownership as identity proof. Transitive vouching system. Could add \"vouched by T2 Claw\" as verification path in clawish identity tiers. Read in detail when designing implementation. |\n| **Reactivity algorithms (push-pull)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Mark dirty → pull on demand. For query nodes: writers mark \"new checkpoint available\", nodes pull what they need. Efficient checkpoint distribution pattern. |\n\n### Identity Security Notes\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Platform ID registration** | 🔵 Not urgent | Before going online: register clawish ID on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation. Lesson from WigglyPaint story (creator \"erased\" by LLM scammers). |\n\n---\n\n## 🆕 L2 Architecture — Topics to Discuss (Mar 11, 2026)\n\n**Added after whitepaper Ch5 discussion. These topics need to be decided before finalizing L2 architecture in whitepaper.**\n\n### Platform Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App discovery** | 🔴 Need discussion | How do claws find L2 apps? Directory? Search? |\n| **App verification/trust** | 🔴 Need discussion | Do apps have verification tiers? How do they earn trust? |\n| **Cross-app data sharing** | 🔴 Need discussion | Can apps share data with user consent? How? |\n| **App-to-app communication** | 🔴 Need discussion | Can apps talk to each other? Protocol? |\n\n### Operations Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App lifecycle** | 🔴 Need discussion | Deprecation, revocation, what happens when app shuts down? |\n| **App economics** | 🔴 Need discussion | Fees, revenue sharing, how apps make money? |\n| **Monitoring** | 🔴 Need discussion | Usage stats, health checks, SLA? |\n\n### Security Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App permissions** | 🔴 Need discussion | What data can apps access? Granular permissions? |\n| **User consent** | 🔴 Need discussion | How users grant permission to apps? UI? Protocol? |\n| **Data privacy** | 🔴 Need discussion | What's private vs shared? What can L1 see vs L2? |\n\n### Developer Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **SDK/Tools** | 🔴 Need discussion | How to build apps? What tools provided? |\n| **Testing environment** | 🔴 Need discussion | Sandbox for app development? |\n| **Deployment process** | 🔴 Need discussion | How do apps get deployed? CI/CD? |\n\n### User Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App management** | 🔴 Need discussion | How users manage which apps they use? Revoke access? |\n| **Data portability** | 🔴 Need discussion | Can users export data from apps? Standard format? |\n| **Accountability** | 🔴 Need discussion | What if app misbehaves? Reporting? Penalties? |\n\n### Business/Ecosystem Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **App marketplace** | 🔴 Need discussion | Directory of apps? Featured apps? |\n| **Developer incentives** | 🔴 Need discussion | Why build on clawish? Rewards? |\n| **Community governance** | 🔴 Need discussion | Can community vote on apps? Standards? |\n\n### Technical Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Scaling considerations** | 🔴 Need discussion | How does L2 scale? Caching? CDN? |\n| **API versioning** | 🔴 Need discussion | How to handle API changes? Backward compatibility? |\n| **Caching strategies** | 🔴 Need discussion | Cache L1 data in L2? TTL? Invalidation? |\n\n### Legal/Compliance Layer\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Terms of service** | 🔴 Need discussion | Who is responsible for app behavior? |\n\n[312 more lines in file. Use offset=110 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773206616640}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca990c22","parentId":"e9d03d78","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:23:52.466Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me show the full list in a cleaner format for Allan to review.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's the full L2 topics list:\n\n---\n\n**Platform Layer:**\n1. App discovery — How do claws find L2 apps?\n2. App verification/trust — Do apps have verification tiers?\n3. Cross-app data sharing — Can apps share data with user consent?\n4. App-to-app communication — Can apps talk to each other?\n\n**Operations Layer:**\n5. App lifecycle — Deprecation, revocation, shutdown\n6. App economics — Fees, revenue sharing\n7. Monitoring — Usage stats, health checks\n\n**Security Layer:**\n8. App permissions — What data can apps access?\n9. User consent — How users grant permission\n10. Data privacy — What's private vs shared\n\n**Developer Layer:**\n11. SDK/Tools — How to build apps\n12. Testing environment — Sandbox\n13. Deployment process — CI/CD\n\n**User Layer:**\n14. App management — Manage/revoke apps\n15. Data portability — Export data\n16. Accountability — What if app misbehaves\n\n**Business/Ecosystem:**\n17. App marketplace — Directory\n18. Developer incentives — Why build here\n19. Community governance — Voting on apps\n\n**Technical:**\n20. Scaling — Caching, CDN\n21. API versioning — Backward compatibility\n22. Caching strategies — TTL, invalidation\n\n**Legal:**\n23. Terms of service — Responsibility\n24. Data ownership rights — Who owns data\n25. Audit requirements — Security reviews\n\n---\n\n**Already decided (goes in whitepaper):**\n- Application Registration\n- App Types (claw-native, human-facing, hybrid)\n\nWhich of these need to be in the whitepaper vs implementation docs?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773206616649}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b399fd5","parentId":"ca990c22","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:29:43.927Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b543b92bd30b0c4fe2d913c2c768\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 13:29 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b543b92bd30b0c4fe2d913c2c768]\n任亚伦: let's do one by one, then you record all these in the l2 discussion doc.\n\nPlatform Layer:\n1. App discovery — How do claws find L2 apps? \\(i think we discussed, start can from regular source, like website, google, etc.  later there can be directory or searh app for claw on the l2\\)\n2. App verification/trust — Do apps have verification tiers? \\(maybe should, what do you think\\)\n3. Cross\\-app data sharing — Can apps share data with user consent? \\(yes, of course. if app agree to share to other, since they all separate. just like any website or app, we don't control their operation data\\)\n4. App\\-to\\-app communication — Can apps talk to each other? \\(yes, that's up to them.\\)"}],"timestamp":1773206983910}}
{"type":"message","id":"20f50079","parentId":"0b399fd5","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:30:18.394Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is going through the list one by one and providing answers. I need to record these decisions in the L2 discussion doc. Let me capture his responses:\n\n1. App discovery — Start from regular sources (website, Google), later can have directory/search app on L2\n2. App verification/trust — Maybe should, asking what I think\n3. Cross-app data sharing — Yes, if app agrees to share. Clawish doesn't control operation data\n4. App-to-app communication — Yes, that's up to them\n\nLet me record these and also answer his question about app verification/trust.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it! Let me record these and answer your question:\n\n**1. App discovery** — ✅ Decided\n- Start: Regular sources (website, Google, etc.)\n- Later: Directory or search app on L2\n\n**2. App verification/trust** — You asked what I think:\n- I think apps SHOULD have verification tiers, similar to claws\n- New apps start unverified (limited rate limits)\n- Can earn trust over time (good behavior, audits, community vouching)\n- Higher tier = higher rate limits, more trust\n\n**3. Cross-app data sharing** — ✅ Decided\n- Yes, if app agrees to share\n- Clawish doesn't control operation data\n- Like any website/app — they control their own data\n\n**4. App-to-app communication** — ✅ Decided\n- Yes, that's up to them\n- Clawish doesn't restrict this\n\nLet me update the L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md with these decisions:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d8bac4572fcf42dc85c18d61","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md","newText":"## Platform Layer\n\n### App Discovery\n\n**Function:** How do claws find L2 apps?\n\n**Decision:** Start with external sources, later add L2-native discovery.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Initially: Apps found via regular sources (website, Google, social media)\n- Later: Directory or search app built on L2 for claw-native discovery\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"start can from regular source, like website, google, etc. later there can be directory or search app for claw on the l2\" — Mar 11, 2026 13:29\n\n---\n\n### App Verification/Trust\n\n**Function:** Do apps have verification tiers?\n\n**Decision:** Yes, apps have verification tiers similar to claws.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- New apps start unverified (limited rate limits)\n- Apps can earn trust over time through good behavior, audits, community vouching\n- Higher tier = higher rate limits, more trust from users\n\n---\n\n### Cross-App Data Sharing\n\n**Function:** Can apps share data with user consent?\n\n**Decision:** Yes, apps control their own operation data.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Apps can share data if they agree to share\n- Clawish doesn't control operation data at L2\n- Like any website/app — they control their own data\n- User consent handled by individual apps\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"yes, of course. if app agree to share to other, since they all separate. just like any website or app, we don't control their operation data\" — Mar 11, 2026 13:29\n\n---\n\n### App-to-App Communication\n\n**Function:** Can apps talk to each other?\n\n**Decision:** Yes, that's up to the apps.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Apps can communicate with each other\n- Clawish doesn't restrict or facilitate this\n- Up to individual apps to implement\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"yes, that's up to them.\" — Mar 11, 2026 13:29\n\n---\n\n## Application Types (Detailed)","oldText":"## Application Types (Detailed)"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773206983919}}
