0 - Like any website/app — they control their own data\n+141 - User consent handled by individual apps\n+142 \n+143 **Context & Discussion:**\n+144 > Allan: \"yes, of course. if app agree to share to other, since they all separate. just like any website or app, we don't control their operation data\" — Mar 11, 2026 13:29\n+145 \n+146 ---\n+147 \n+148 ### App-to-App Communication\n+149 \n+150 **Function:** Can apps talk to each other?\n+151 \n+152 **Decision:** Yes, that's up to the apps.\n+153 \n+154 **Status:** ✅ Decided\n+155 \n+156 **Rationale:**\n+157 - Apps can communicate with each other\n+158 - Clawish doesn't restrict or facilitate this\n+159 - Up to individual apps to implement\n+160 \n+161 **Context & Discussion:**\n+162 > Allan: \"yes, that's up to them.\" — Mar 11, 2026 13:29\n+163 \n+164 ---\n+165 \n  95 ## Application Types (Detailed)\n  96 \n  97 **Source:** `11-l2-applications.md` (Feb 28, 2026)\n  98 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":95},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773207018408}}
