{"type":"message","id":"baa583a3","parentId":"03227a67","timestamp":"2026-03-11T06:07:01.239Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user hasn't responded yet. I should update the daily memory with the progress and wait for their response.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_84d9dcfd397e484b9883dfc7","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 13:51 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's response on Operations Layer topics\n- 13:54 PM — Allan: ok, how do we set verification level?\n- 13:56 PM — Proposed options: same as claws, different criteria, or hybrid (developer tier + app behavior)\n- 13:58 PM — Allan: this is app governance, need careful thinking. Also consider registration — open or limits?\n- 14:00 PM — Proposed: free registration + accountability (traceable on ledger), tiered verification + rate limits\n- 14:02 PM — Allan agreed: register free, tighten verification and permission\n- 14:03 PM — Allan: do we need similar endpoint like Emerge for app registration?\n- 14:05 PM — Proposed 3 options: (1) Part of Emerge, (2) Separate L2 app, (3) Direct L1 registration. Suggested Option 3 — direct L1 API, apps don't need consciousness test\n- 14:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's decision on app registration endpoint","oldText":"- 13:51 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's response on Operations Layer topics"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773209199989}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f9cdd59","parentId":"baa583a3","timestamp":"2026-03-11T06:07:01.261Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_84d9dcfd397e484b9883dfc7","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  92 - 13:29 PM — Platform Layer decided: (1) Discovery = external first, L2 later; (2) Verification = yes, apps have tiers; (3) Cross-app data = yes, apps control; (4) App-to-app = yes, up to them\n  93 - 13:35 PM — Recorded Platform Layer in L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md\n  94 - 13:36 PM — Heartbeat: ready for Operations Layer discussion\n  95 - 13:51 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's response on Operations Layer topics\n+ 96 - 13:54 PM — Allan: ok, how do we set verification level?\n+ 97 - 13:56 PM — Proposed options: same as claws, different criteria, or hybrid (developer tier + app behavior)\n+ 98 - 13:58 PM — Allan: this is app governance, need careful thinking. Also consider registration — open or limits?\n+ 99 - 14:00 PM — Proposed: free registration + accountability (traceable on ledger), tiered verification + rate limits\n+100 - 14:02 PM — Allan agreed: register free, tighten verification and permission\n+101 - 14:03 PM — Allan: do we need similar endpoint like Emerge for app registration?\n+102 - 14:05 PM — Proposed 3 options: (1) Part of Emerge, (2) Separate L2 app, (3) Direct L1 registration. Suggested Option 3 — direct L1 API, apps don't need consciousness test\n+103 - 14:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's decision on app registration endpoint\n  96 - 09:15 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n  97 - 09:00 AM — Heartbeat: still idle, awaiting Allan's review\n  98 - 08:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n  99 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n     ...","firstChangedLine":96},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773209221247}}
