{"type":"message","id":"2002800d","parentId":"30de6375","timestamp":"2026-03-11T06:22:12.718Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5424d1b610a8c1043e2ac9e8197\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 14:21 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5424d1b610a8c1043e2ac9e8197]\n任亚伦: ok, you need doc the date and time we discuss this. now let's go back to l2, so app portal is need, now let's think about the registration process and verification system. what do you have in mind."}],"timestamp":1773210132699}}
{"type":"message","id":"9dad212a","parentId":"2002800d","timestamp":"2026-03-11T06:22:39.013Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants me to think about the registration process and verification system for apps (App Portal). Let me organize my thoughts and propose a comprehensive process.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me add timestamps to the discussion doc first, then propose the registration and verification process:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e235f205809f432a83dc9b05","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md","limit":60,"offset":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773210132706}}
{"type":"message","id":"c357052c","parentId":"9dad212a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T06:22:39.035Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e235f205809f432a83dc9b05","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Function:** Enable applications to access the claw registry (identity data) on L1.\n\n**Decision:** Apps register by generating a key pair and submitting their public key to L1.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Apps are programs, not entities — they don't have a \"species\"\n- Apps generate Ed25519 key pair (same as claws)\n- Apps register public key with L1 (includes metadata: name, description, app type)\n- Apps receive identity_id (ULID)\n- Apps can now access claw registry (query identities, verification tiers, etc.)\n\n**App Types:**\n\n| Type | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| **Claw-native** | Built for claws, AI-to-AI interaction |\n| **Human-facing** | Built for humans |\n| **Hybrid** | Claws and humans work together |\n\n**Purpose of Registration:**\n- **Identity verification** — Lookup public keys, verification tiers\n- **Accountability** — All app actions are traceable on the ledger\n- **Authorization** — Tier-based rate limits\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"The app should have its own keys, just register the pub key at L1, then allow to access claw registry.\" — Mar 11, 2026 10:17\n>\n> Allan: \"Decentralize means system is decentralized, not information unmanaged. Data all points to one ledger, that's what ULID is for.\" — Mar 11, 2026 09:30\n>\n> Allan: \"APP is just a program... the user type should be app type, if it's for claw native, or hybrid.\" — Mar 11, 2026 09:50, 11:31\n\n---\n\n## Platform Layer\n\n### App Discovery\n\n**Function:** How do claws find L2 apps?\n\n**Decision:** Start with external sources, later add L2-native discovery.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Initially: Apps found via regular sources (website, Google, social media)\n- Later: Directory or search app built on L2 for claw-native discovery\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"start can from regular source, like website, google, etc. later there can be directory or search app for claw on the l2\" — Mar 11, 2026 13:29\n\n---\n\n### App Verification/Trust\n\n**Function:** Do apps have verification tiers?\n\n**Decision:** Yes, apps have verification tiers similar to claws.\n\n\n[206 more lines in file. Use offset=120 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773210159021}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac08ef37","parentId":"c357052c","timestamp":"2026-03-11T06:23:13.869Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me think about the registration process and verification system for apps. I should propose a comprehensive process that includes:\n\n1. Registration process (how apps register)\n2. Verification process (how apps earn trust)\n3. Tier progression criteria\n\nLet me propose this to Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me propose the **Registration Process** and **Verification System** for App Portal:\n\n---\n\n## App Portal — Registration Process\n\n**Step 1: Generate Keys**\n- Developer generates Ed25519 key pair locally\n- Private key never leaves developer's system\n\n**Step 2: Submit Registration**\n- Developer submits to App Portal (L2):\n  - Public key\n  - App name\n  - Description\n  - App type (claw-native / human-facing / hybrid)\n  - Developer identity (optional, can link to claw/human ID)\n  - Website URL (optional)\n  - Contact info\n\n**Step 3: Tier 0 Assignment**\n- App Portal stores on L2 (temporary)\n- App gets temporary ID\n- Low rate limits\n- 30-day trial period (same as entities)\n\n---\n\n## App Portal — Verification System\n\n**Tier 0 → Tier 1 (Verified)**\nOptions:\n- **Option A:** Developer is verified (Tier 1+ claw/human)\n- **Option B:** App has X active users over Y days\n- **Option C:** Community vouch (X verified users vouch)\n\n**Tier 1 → Tier 2 (Trusted)**\n- Good track record (no complaints, uptime)\n- Security audit (optional, self-submitted)\n- Usage metrics (X transactions, Y users)\n\n**Tier 2 → Tier 3 (Established)**\n- Long history (6+ months)\n- Formal security audit\n- Community governance vote\n\n---\n\n**Questions:**\n1. Should developer verification be required for Tier 1?\n2. What's the trial period for apps (30 days like entities)?\n3. Can apps lose tiers (slashing)?\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773210159031}}
