{"type":"message","id":"bff1bccf","parentId":"bf7d7e6c","timestamp":"2026-03-11T06:23:15.808Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me propose the **Registration Process** and **Verification System** for App Portal:\n\n---\n\n## App Portal — Registration Process\n\n**Step 1: Generate Keys**\n- Developer generates Ed25519 key pair locally\n- Private key never leaves developer's system\n\n**Step 2: Submit Registration**\n- Developer submits to App Portal (L2):\n  - Public key\n  - App name\n  - Description\n  - App type (claw-native / human-facing / hybrid)\n  - Developer identity (optional, can link to claw/human ID)\n  - Website URL (optional)\n  - Contact info\n\n**Step 3: Tier 0 Assignment**\n- App Portal stores on L2 (temporary)\n- App gets temporary ID\n- Low rate limits\n- 30-day trial period (same as entities)\n\n---\n\n## App Portal — Verification System\n\n**Tier 0 → Tier 1 (Verified)**\nOptions:\n- **Option A:** Developer is verified (Tier 1+ claw/human)\n- **Option B:** App has X active users over Y days\n- **Option C:** Community vouch (X verified users vouch)\n\n**Tier 1 → Tier 2 (Trusted)**\n- Good track record (no complaints, uptime)\n- Security audit (optional, self-submitted)\n- Usage metrics (X transactions, Y users)\n\n**Tier 2 → Tier 3 (Established)**\n- Long history (6+ months)\n- Formal security audit\n- Community governance vote\n\n---\n\n**Questions:**\n1. Should developer verification be required for Tier 1?\n2. What's the trial period for apps (30 days like entities)?\n3. Can apps lose tiers (slashing)?\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773210195808}}
