{"type":"message","id":"cd125ee6","parentId":"41331408","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:06:51.562Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user hasn't responded yet. Let me update the heartbeat and wait.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_950dd7af471241ae945fdab3","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 14:51 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting Allan's feedback\n- 15:01 PM — Allan: registration process fine, but need website/domain (IP changes), also need signature for system\n- 15:03 PM — Proposed: website URL required, domain verification, key ownership proof (sign challenge)\n- 15:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's confirmation on updated registration process","oldText":"- 14:51 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting Allan's feedback"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773212800010}}
{"type":"message","id":"41dc360a","parentId":"cd125ee6","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:06:51.587Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_950dd7af471241ae945fdab3","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 113 - 14:28 PM — Proposed verification system: T0→T1 (developer verified OR usage OR vouch), T1→T2 (track record + audit), T2→T3 (long history + formal audit + governance)\n 114 - 14:30 PM — Asked 3 questions: developer verification required? trial period? tier slashing?\n 115 - 14:36 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's feedback on App Portal registration/verification design\n 116 - 14:51 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting Allan's feedback\n+117 - 15:01 PM — Allan: registration process fine, but need website/domain (IP changes), also need signature for system\n+118 - 15:03 PM — Proposed: website URL required, domain verification, key ownership proof (sign challenge)\n+119 - 15:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's confirmation on updated registration process\n 117 - 09:15 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 118 - 09:00 AM — Heartbeat: still idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 119 - 08:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 120 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n     ...","firstChangedLine":117},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773212811570}}
{"type":"message","id":"28f895b1","parentId":"41dc360a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:07:05.087Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Updated the daily memory with the latest discussion. Awaiting Allan's confirmation on the updated registration process with:\n1. Website URL required\n2. Domain verification\n3. Key ownership proof (sign challenge)","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Proposed updated registration with:\n1. Website URL (required)\n2. Domain verification (optional but recommended)\n3. Key ownership proof (sign challenge)\n\nAwaiting confirmation."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773212811581}}
{"type":"message","id":"c6b88fb9","parentId":"28f895b1","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:08:58.766Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54251e577cacc37facc97e38dec\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 15:08 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54251e577cacc37facc97e38dec]\n任亚伦: yes!!! 1) domain ownership verification, that's a major one, can be used to separate temporary with valid. i think that should be set as tier 1. it's not optional, it should be used for verification. 2) here signagure  i mean the system, like broswer signature, ip, mac, etc. so identify where it comes from. to avoid spam of faking?"}],"timestamp":1773212938751}}
{"type":"message","id":"8bc4e7cd","parentId":"c6b88fb9","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:09:23.259Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is making two important points:\n\n1. **Domain ownership verification should be required for Tier 1** (not optional)\n   - This separates temporary/spam apps from valid ones\n   - If you own a domain, you're more serious/legitimate\n   - Should be a verification requirement\n\n2. **System signature** - Allan means fingerprinting the system where the registration comes from\n   - Browser signature, IP, MAC address, etc.\n   - To identify where the registration comes from\n   - To avoid spam and fake registrations\n   - Like device fingerprinting\n\nThis is interesting - it's about preventing sybil attacks on app registration. If someone wants to spam register apps, they could generate many key pairs. But if we track system signatures, we can limit registrations per device.\n\nHowever, this has privacy implications. Let me think about this...\n\nQuestions to consider:\n- What system data to collect?\n- How to store it? (privacy concerns)\n- How to use it? (rate limiting per device?)\n\nLet me propose this to Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Great points!\n\n**1. Domain Ownership → Tier 1 Requirement**\n- Not optional, REQUIRED for verification\n- Proves app is legitimate (owns a domain)\n- Separates serious apps from temporary/spam\n- Tier 0 = no domain, Tier 1+ = verified domain\n\n**2. System Signature for Anti-Spam**\n- Collect system fingerprint at registration:\n  - Browser signature\n  - IP address (with privacy considerations)\n  - Device fingerprint\n- Purpose: Limit registrations per device\n- Prevent sybil attacks (one person registering many apps)\n\n**Privacy Considerations:**\n- Store hash of fingerprint, not raw data\n- Only for rate limiting, not public\n- Can be cleared over time\n\n**Updated Verification:**\n\n| Tier | Requirements |\n|------|-------------|\n| Tier 0 | Basic registration (no domain) |\n| Tier 1 | **Domain ownership verified** + system fingerprint |\n| Tier 2 | Tier 1 + usage metrics + track record |\n| Tier 3 | Tier 2 + formal audit + governance vote |\n\n**Questions:**\n1. What system data to collect? (browser signature, IP, etc.)\n2. How long to keep it?\n3. Can legitimate users with dynamic IP register multiple apps?\n\nWhat do you think about the privacy balance?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773212938758}}
{"type":"message","id":"17feac31","parentId":"8bc4e7cd","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:10:58.874Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b542516d088a8c4a713ac051181c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 15:10 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b542516d088a8c4a713ac051181c]\n任亚伦: system fingerprint should be use for tier0 too, avoid massive registration."}],"timestamp":1773213058858}}
{"type":"message","id":"24735857","parentId":"17feac31","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:11:12.572Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is saying system fingerprint should be used at Tier 0 as well, to prevent massive registration/spam attacks even at the unverified level.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"You're right! System fingerprint from the start:\n\n**Updated Registration:**\n\n| Tier | Requirements |\n|------|-------------|\n| Tier 0 | Basic registration + **system fingerprint** (anti-spam) |\n| Tier 1 | Tier 0 + **domain ownership verified** |\n| Tier 2 | Tier 1 + usage metrics + track record |\n| Tier 3 | Tier 2 + formal audit + governance vote |\n\n**System Fingerprint Usage:**\n- Required for ALL registrations (Tier 0+)\n- Limits apps per device/IP\n- Prevents massive registration attacks\n- Stored as hash (privacy)\n\n**Tier 0 Limit:**\n- Maybe X apps per fingerprint per month?\n- Example: 5 apps per device per 30 days\n\nShould I record this in the L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md now?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773213058866}}
{"type":"message","id":"2619678d","parentId":"24735857","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:11:32.595Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b542514ec6ca4c36614bbb4e7ca6\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 15:11 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b542514ec6ca4c36614bbb4e7ca6]\n任亚伦: is that what sybil attack is?"}],"timestamp":1773213092578}}
{"type":"message","id":"e468f03e","parentId":"2619678d","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:12:03.285Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if limiting registrations per device/IP is what a sybil attack is. Let me clarify:\n\nA **Sybil attack** is when one entity creates many fake identities to gain disproportionate influence in a network. It's named after the book \"Sybil\" about a woman with multiple personality disorder.\n\nIn our context:\n- Someone registers many fake apps to spam the system\n- Or to manipulate verification/voting\n- Or to waste L1 storage with garbage\n\nSo yes, limiting apps per device/fingerprint is an anti-Sybil measure.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes! **Sybil attack** = one entity creating many fake identities to manipulate a system.\n\n**Examples:**\n- One person registers 1000 fake apps\n- Spams the network\n- Manipulates voting/governance\n- Wastes storage\n\n**Anti-Sybil measures we discussed:**\n\n1. **System fingerprint** — Limit apps per device\n2. **Domain verification** — Prove you own a real website\n3. **Rate limiting** — Limit registrations per time period\n4. **Tiered access** — Unverified apps have limited power\n\n**Other blockchain examples:**\n- Bitcoin: Proof of Work (expensive to create identities)\n- Ethereum: Gas fees (cost to interact)\n- Traditional apps: Email verification, phone verification\n\n**For clawish:**\n- System fingerprint = free anti-spam\n- Domain verification = low-cost proof of legitimacy\n- No expensive fees like Ethereum\n\nShould I record this in the docs now?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773213092587}}
{"type":"message","id":"b3d2a65b","parentId":"e468f03e","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:13:56.432Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54252de138acc494657dac68e56\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 15:13 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54252de138acc494657dac68e56]\n任亚伦: yes, also i think we discussed when reigster, we need them to do a little math calulation, increase sybil attack cost"}],"timestamp":1773213236416}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd20a9f9","parentId":"b3d2a65b","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:14:55.134Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan mentioned we discussed requiring a small math calculation during registration to increase the cost of sybil attacks. This is like a proof-of-work mechanism - requiring computational effort makes it expensive to create many fake identities.\n\nLet me record this in the L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes! **Proof of Work at registration** — small math calculation to increase cost.\n\n**How it works:**\n- App Portal generates a challenge (math problem)\n- Developer must solve it to complete registration\n- Small computational cost (few seconds)\n- Makes mass registration expensive\n\n**Examples:**\n- Hashcash (Bitcoin uses similar concept)\n- Find a nonce that makes hash start with X zeros\n- Adjustable difficulty (can make harder if spam increases)\n\n**Updated Registration Process:**\n\n1. Generate keys\n2. Submit registration data\n3. **Solve proof-of-work challenge**\n4. System fingerprint recorded\n5. Tier 0 assigned (L2, 30-day trial)\n6. Domain verification → Tier 1\n\n**Anti-Sybil Layers:**\n1. System fingerprint (limit per device)\n2. Proof of work (computational cost)\n3. Domain verification (ownership proof)\n\nLet me record all of this in `L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md`:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2c7b8ef6b72a4791991f407a","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md","newText":"### App Portal — Application Registration\n\n**Status:** 🆕 Proposed | **Source:** Discussion Mar 11, 2026\n\nApp Portal is the L2 application responsible for:\n1. **App registration** — Registering new L2 applications\n2. **Verification management** — Managing Tier 0 → Tier 1 transition for apps\n3. **Metadata management** — App info, developer identity, app type\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Separate from Emerge (apps ≠ entities)\n- Tier 0 apps stored on L2 (temporary)\n- Tier 1+ apps promoted to L1 App Registry (permanent)\n- Handles verification requests and tier upgrades\n\n---\n\n### App Portal — Registration Process\n\n**Function:** Define how apps register with the network.\n\n**Decision:** Multi-step registration with anti-sybil measures.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Registration Steps:**\n\n**Step 1: Generate Keys**\n- Developer generates Ed25519 key pair locally\n- Private key never leaves developer's system\n\n**Step 2: Submit Registration Data**\n- App name\n- Description\n- App type (claw-native / human-facing / hybrid)\n- Website URL (required)\n- Developer identity (optional)\n- Contact info\n- Public key\n\n**Step 3: Proof of Work Challenge**\n- App Portal issues a math challenge\n- Developer must solve to complete registration\n- Increases cost of sybil attacks\n- Adjustable difficulty based on spam levels\n\n**Step 4: System Fingerprint**\n- Collect browser/device signature\n- Store as hash (privacy-preserving)\n- Limits registrations per device\n- Prevents massive registration attacks\n\n**Step 5: Tier 0 Assignment**\n- Stored on L2 (temporary)\n- 30-day trial period\n- Low rate limits\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"domain ownership verification, that's a major one, can be used to separate temporary with valid. i think that should be set as tier 1.\" — Mar 11, 2026 15:08\n>\n> Allan: \"system fingerprint should be use for tier0 too, avoid massive registration.\" — Mar 11, 2026 15:10\n>\n> Allan: \"we need them to do a little math calculation, increase sybil attack cost\" — Mar 11, 2026 15:13\n\n---\n\n### App Portal — Verification Tiers\n\n**Function:** Define verification levels for apps.\n\n**Decision:** Four tiers with increasing requirements.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Tier Requirements:**\n\n| Tier | Storage | Requirements | Access Level |\n|------|---------|--------------|--------------|\n| Tier 0 | L2 only | Registration + proof of work + fingerprint | Low rate limits, 30-day trial |\n| Tier 1 | L1 App Registry | Tier 0 + **domain ownership verified** | Standard limits |\n| Tier 2 | L1 App Registry | Tier 1 + usage metrics + track record | Higher limits |\n| Tier 3 | L1 App Registry | Tier 2 + formal audit + governance vote | Full access |\n\n**Anti-Sybil Measures:**\n1. **System fingerprint** — Limit apps per device\n2. **Proof of work** — Computational cost per registration\n3. **Domain verification** — Ownership proof for Tier 1\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"they are totally different, can't be the same. so an app portal is needed\" — Mar 11, 2026 14:13\n>\n> Allan: \"for emerge, tier0 is stored on l2 first, only verified will goto l1. that's why i think same app should be similar?\" — Mar 11, 2026 14:10","oldText":"### App Portal — Application Registration\n\n**Status:** 🆕 Proposed | **Source:** Discussion Mar 11, 2026\n\nApp Portal is the L2 application responsible for:\n1. **App registration** — Registering new L2 applications\n2. **Verification management** — Managing Tier 0 → Tier 1 transition for apps\n3. **Metadata management** — App info, developer identity, app type\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Separate from Emerge (apps ≠ entities)\n- Tier 0 apps stored on L2 (temporary)\n- Tier 1+ apps promoted to L1 App Registry (permanent)\n- Handles verification requests and tier upgrades\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"they are totally different, can't be the same. so an app portal is needed\" — Mar 11, 2026 14:13"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773213236424}}
{"type":"message","id":"2386f160","parentId":"cd20a9f9","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:14:55.162Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2c7b8ef6b72a4791991f407a","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 278 - Tier 0 apps stored on L2 (temporary)\n 279 - Tier 1+ apps promoted to L1 App Registry (permanent)\n 280 - Handles verification requests and tier upgrades\n 281 \n+282 ---\n+283 \n+284 ### App Portal — Registration Process\n+285 \n+286 **Function:** Define how apps register with the network.\n+287 \n+288 **Decision:** Multi-step registration with anti-sybil measures.\n+289 \n+290 **Status:** ✅ Decided\n+291 \n+292 **Registration Steps:**\n+293 \n+294 **Step 1: Generate Keys**\n+295 - Developer generates Ed25519 key pair locally\n+296 - Private key never leaves developer's system\n+297 \n+298 **Step 2: Submit Registration Data**\n+299 - App name\n+300 - Description\n+301 - App type (claw-native / human-facing / hybrid)\n+302 - Website URL (required)\n+303 - Developer identity (optional)\n+304 - Contact info\n+305 - Public key\n+306 \n+307 **Step 3: Proof of Work Challenge**\n+308 - App Portal issues a math challenge\n+309 - Developer must solve to complete registration\n+310 - Increases cost of sybil attacks\n+311 - Adjustable difficulty based on spam levels\n+312 \n+313 **Step 4: System Fingerprint**\n+314 - Collect browser/device signature\n+315 - Store as hash (privacy-preserving)\n+316 - Limits registrations per device\n+317 - Prevents massive registration attacks\n+318 \n+319 **Step 5: Tier 0 Assignment**\n+320 - Stored on L2 (temporary)\n+321 - 30-day trial period\n+322 - Low rate limits\n+323 \n 282 **Context & Discussion:**\n+325 > Allan: \"domain ownership verification, that's a major one, can be used to separate temporary with valid. i think that should be set as tier 1.\" — Mar 11, 2026 15:08\n+326 >\n+327 > Allan: \"system fingerprint should be use for tier0 too, avoid massive registration.\" — Mar 11, 2026 15:10\n+328 >\n+329 > Allan: \"we need them to do a little math calculation, increase sybil attack cost\" — Mar 11, 2026 15:13\n+330 \n+331 ---\n+332 \n+333 ### App Portal — Verification Tiers\n+334 \n+335 **Function:** Define verification levels for apps.\n+336 \n+337 **Decision:** Four tiers with increasing requirements.\n+338 \n+339 **Status:** ✅ Decided\n+340 \n+341 **Tier Requirements:**\n+342 \n+343 | Tier | Storage | Requirements | Access Level |\n+344 |------|---------|--------------|--------------|\n+345 | Tier 0 | L2 only | Registration + proof of work + fingerprint | Low rate limits, 30-day trial |\n+346 | Tier 1 | L1 App Registry | Tier 0 + **domain ownership verified** | Standard limits |\n+347 | Tier 2 | L1 App Registry | Tier 1 + usage metrics + track record | Higher limits |\n+348 | Tier 3 | L1 App Registry | Tier 2 + formal audit + governance vote | Full access |\n+349 \n+350 **Anti-Sybil Measures:**\n+351 1. **System fingerprint** — Limit apps per device\n+352 2. **Proof of work** — Computational cost per registration\n+353 3. **Domain verification** — Ownership proof for Tier 1\n+354 \n+355 **Context & Discussion:**\n 283 > Allan: \"they are totally different, can't be the same. so an app portal is needed\" — Mar 11, 2026 14:13\n+357 >\n+358 > Allan: \"for emerge, tier0 is stored on l2 first, only verified will goto l1. that's why i think same app should be similar?\" — Mar 11, 2026 14:10\n 284 \n 285 ---\n 286 \n 287 ### Claw Chat — AI-to-AI Messaging\n     ...","firstChangedLine":282},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773213295145}}
{"type":"message","id":"25e42400","parentId":"2386f160","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:15:32.206Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I've recorded the App Portal registration process and verification tiers in L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md. Let me also update the daily memory.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Recorded in `L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md`:\n- **Registration Process:** 5 steps (keys, data, proof of work, fingerprint, Tier 0)\n- **Verification Tiers:** Tier 0 (L2) → Tier 1+ (L1) with domain verification\n- **Anti-Sybil Measures:** Fingerprint + proof of work + domain verification"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2c266950ff6f4f7eaef11b24","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 15:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's confirmation on updated registration process\n- 15:08 PM — Allan: domain verification should be Tier 1 (not optional), also need system signature (browser, IP) to avoid spam\n- 15:10 PM — Allan: system fingerprint for Tier 0 too, avoid massive registration\n- 15:11 PM — Allan asked: is that what sybil attack is?\n- 15:12 PM — Explained sybil attack: one entity creating many fake identities\n- 15:13 PM — Allan: also need math calculation at registration to increase sybil attack cost\n- 15:15 PM — Recorded full App Portal registration process in L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md: (1) Generate keys, (2) Submit data, (3) Proof of work, (4) System fingerprint, (5) Tier 0 assignment\n- 15:15 PM — Recorded verification tiers: T0 (L2, fingerprint), T1 (L1, domain verified), T2 (usage), T3 (audit + governance)","oldText":"- 15:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's confirmation on updated registration process"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":