{"type":"message","id":"6231c71e","parentId":"25e42400","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:15:32.235Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2c266950ff6f4f7eaef11b24","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 116 - 14:51 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting Allan's feedback\n 117 - 15:01 PM — Allan: registration process fine, but need website/domain (IP changes), also need signature for system\n 118 - 15:03 PM — Proposed: website URL required, domain verification, key ownership proof (sign challenge)\n 119 - 15:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's confirmation on updated registration process\n+120 - 15:08 PM — Allan: domain verification should be Tier 1 (not optional), also need system signature (browser, IP) to avoid spam\n+121 - 15:10 PM — Allan: system fingerprint for Tier 0 too, avoid massive registration\n+122 - 15:11 PM — Allan asked: is that what sybil attack is?\n+123 - 15:12 PM — Explained sybil attack: one entity creating many fake identities\n+124 - 15:13 PM — Allan: also need math calculation at registration to increase sybil attack cost\n+125 - 15:15 PM — Recorded full App Portal registration process in L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md: (1) Generate keys, (2) Submit data, (3) Proof of work, (4) System fingerprint, (5) Tier 0 assignment\n+126 - 15:15 PM — Recorded verification tiers: T0 (L2, fingerprint), T1 (L1, domain verified), T2 (usage), T3 (audit + governance)\n 120 - 09:15 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 121 - 09:00 AM — Heartbeat: still idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 122 - 08:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 123 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n     ...","firstChangedLine":120},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773213332215}}
