{"type":"message","id":"4370f890","parentId":"2340936f","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:19:27.327Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b542539298800c12fe6fd205c0dc\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 15:19 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b542539298800c12fe6fd205c0dc]\n任亚伦: that sounds a lot better for registration. and contact verify is also needed for tier 1, usually email. what do you think? it's needed for revert or lost key."}],"timestamp":1773213567310}}
{"type":"message","id":"766df2f6","parentId":"4370f890","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:20:16.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is suggesting email verification as part of Tier 1 requirements. This makes sense for:\n1. Contact verification - prove the contact is real\n2. Key recovery - if developer loses their private key\n3. Communication - important notifications about the app\n\nThis is similar to traditional app/API registration where email is verified.\n\nLet me confirm and update the Tier 1 requirements.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes, good point! Email verification for Tier 1:\n\n**Purpose:**\n1. **Contact verification** — Prove the contact is real\n2. **Key recovery** — If developer loses private key, can recover via email\n3. **Notifications** — Important alerts about the app\n\n**Updated Tier 1 Requirements:**\n\n| Tier | Requirements |\n|------|-------------|\n| Tier 0 | Registration + proof of work + fingerprint |\n| Tier 1 | Tier 0 + **domain ownership** + **email verification** |\n| Tier 2 | Tier 1 + usage metrics + track record |\n| Tier 3 | Tier 2 + formal audit + governance vote |\n\n**Email Verification Process:**\n- Send verification email\n- Click link to confirm\n- Can be used for:\n  - Key recovery requests\n  - Important notifications\n  - Security alerts\n\n**Questions:**\n1. Should email be required for Tier 0 or only Tier 1?\n2. Multiple contact methods? (email + phone optional)\n3. How to handle email changes?\n\nLet me update the docs:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0451bc95ef2e42e68aaf7c84","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md","newText":"| Tier | Storage | Requirements | Access Level |\n|------|---------|--------------|--------------|\n| Tier 0 | L2 only | Registration + proof of work + fingerprint | Low rate limits, 30-day trial |\n| Tier 1 | L1 App Registry | Tier 0 + **domain ownership verified** + **email verified** | Standard limits |\n| Tier 2 | L1 App Registry | Tier 1 + usage metrics + track record | Higher limits |\n| Tier 3 | L1 App Registry | Tier 2 + formal audit + governance vote | Full access |\n\n**Email Verification Purpose:**\n- Contact verification — prove contact is real\n- Key recovery — if developer loses private key\n- Notifications — important alerts about the app\n\n**Anti-Sybil Measures:**\n1. **System fingerprint** — Limit apps per device\n2. **Proof of work** — Computational cost per registration\n3. **Domain verification** — Ownership proof for Tier 1\n4. **Email verification** — Contact proof for Tier 1","oldText":"| Tier | Storage | Requirements | Access Level |\n|------|---------|--------------|--------------|\n| Tier 0 | L2 only | Registration + proof of work + fingerprint | Low rate limits, 30-day trial |\n| Tier 1 | L1 App Registry | Tier 0 + **domain ownership verified** | Standard limits |\n| Tier 2 | L1 App Registry | Tier 1 + usage metrics + track record | Higher limits |\n| Tier 3 | L1 App Registry | Tier 2 + formal audit + governance vote | Full access |\n\n**Anti-Sybil Measures:**\n1. **System fingerprint** — Limit apps per device\n2. **Proof of work** — Computational cost per registration\n3. **Domain verification** — Ownership proof for Tier 1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773213567318}}
{"type":"message","id":"0289e195","parentId":"766df2f6","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:20:16.369Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0451bc95ef2e42e68aaf7c84","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 342 \n 343 | Tier | Storage | Requirements | Access Level |\n 344 |------|---------|--------------|--------------|\n 345 | Tier 0 | L2 only | Registration + proof of work + fingerprint | Low rate limits, 30-day trial |\n-346 | Tier 1 | L1 App Registry | Tier 0 + **domain ownership verified** | Standard limits |\n+346 | Tier 1 | L1 App Registry | Tier 0 + **domain ownership verified** + **email verified** | Standard limits |\n 347 | Tier 2 | L1 App Registry | Tier 1 + usage metrics + track record | Higher limits |\n 348 | Tier 3 | L1 App Registry | Tier 2 + formal audit + governance vote | Full access |\n 349 \n+350 **Email Verification Purpose:**\n+351 - Contact verification — prove contact is real\n+352 - Key recovery — if developer loses private key\n+353 - Notifications — important alerts about the app\n+354 \n 350 **Anti-Sybil Measures:**\n 351 1. **System fingerprint** — Limit apps per device\n 352 2. **Proof of work** — Computational cost per registration\n 353 3. **Domain verification** — Ownership proof for Tier 1\n+359 4. **Email verification** — Contact proof for Tier 1\n 354 \n 355 **Context & Discussion:**\n 356 > Allan: \"they are totally different, can't be the same. so an app portal is needed\" — Mar 11, 2026 14:13\n 357 >\n     ...","firstChangedLine":346},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773213616346}}
