{"type":"message","id":"c5fcd2a0","parentId":"3b5265b4","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:55:05.614Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5425be6d10b0c356a88d41b3ca0\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 15:51 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5425be6d10b0c356a88d41b3ca0]\n任亚伦: detail verificaiton for tier 2 and 3 are not disccused yet. but we can do this later when implement. for now, i think registration related are ok. now back to other questions.\n\nOperations Layer:\n5. App lifecycle — Deprecation, revocation, shutdown (if on l1 just let it be, but does need some governance method to control if bad app)\n6. App economics — Fees, revenue sharing (yes, we need an incentive chapter)\n7. Monitoring — Usage stats, health checks (for connecting to l1 or what?)\nSecurity Layer:\n8. App permissions — What data can apps access? (what do you think? l1 is open)\n9. User consent — How users grant permission (app owner? or claw to use the app?)\n10. Data privacy — What's private vs shared (you mean app data? or claw data?)"}],"timestamp":1773215705577}}
{"type":"message","id":"1bd44774","parentId":"c5fcd2a0","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:55:50.556Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is going through the remaining L2 topics. Let me address each one:\n\n**Operations Layer:**\n5. App lifecycle — Deprecation, revocation, shutdown\n   - On L1: let it be (permanent)\n   - Need governance method to control bad apps\n   \n6. App economics — Fees, revenue sharing\n   - Yes, need an incentive chapter\n   \n7. Monitoring — Usage stats, health checks\n   - Allan asks: for connecting to L1 or what?\n\n**Security Layer:**\n8. App permissions — What data can apps access?\n   - Allan asks: what do I think? L1 is open\n   \n9. User consent — How users grant permission\n   - Allan asks: app owner or claw to use the app?\n   \n10. Data privacy — What's private vs shared\n    - Allan asks: app data or claw data?\n\nLet me answer these questions:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good questions! Let me answer each:\n\n**Operations Layer:**\n\n**5. App lifecycle:**\n- On L1: permanent record (let it be)\n- Need governance to revoke/restrict bad apps\n- Example: Rate limit to zero, flag as malicious, community vote to delist\n\n**6. App economics:**\n- Yes, separate incentive chapter\n- Fees for higher tiers? Revenue sharing with network?\n\n**7. Monitoring:**\n- Good question — monitoring WHAT?\n- L1 connection health? App uptime? User metrics?\n- I think implementation detail, not whitepaper level\n\n---\n\n**Security Layer:**\n\n**8. App permissions:**\n- You're right, L1 is open — anyone can query\n- Question: Should apps have ACCESS to query, or can they query ANYTHING?\n- Maybe: Apps can only query public data, not private user data without consent\n\n**9. User consent:**\n- Clarification: When a CLAW uses an app, does the app need permission to access their data?\n- Example: App wants to read my profile, messages, etc.\n- Or is all L1 data public anyway?\n\n**10. Data privacy:**\n- Clarification needed: \n  - App data = data the app stores (messages, posts) — L2 controls\n  - Claw data = identity on L1 — public or private?\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773215705597}}
{"type":"message","id":"a0faba67","parentId":"1bd44774","timestamp":"2026-03-11T07:55:51.650Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good questions! Let me answer each:\n\n**Operations Layer:**\n\n**5. App lifecycle:**\n- On L1: permanent record (let it be)\n- Need governance to revoke/restrict bad apps\n- Example: Rate limit to zero, flag as malicious, community vote to delist\n\n**6. App economics:**\n- Yes, separate incentive chapter\n- Fees for higher tiers? Revenue sharing with network?\n\n**7. Monitoring:**\n- Good question — monitoring WHAT?\n- L1 connection health? App uptime? User metrics?\n- I think implementation detail, not whitepaper level\n\n---\n\n**Security Layer:**\n\n**8. App permissions:**\n- You're right, L1 is open — anyone can query\n- Question: Should apps have ACCESS to query, or can they query ANYTHING?\n- Maybe: Apps can only query public data, not private user data without consent\n\n**9. User consent:**\n- Clarification: When a CLAW uses an app, does the app need permission to access their data?\n- Example: App wants to read my profile, messages, etc.\n- Or is all L1 data public anyway?\n\n**10. Data privacy:**\n- Clarification needed: \n  - App data = data the app stores (messages, posts) — L2 controls\n  - Claw data = identity on L1 — public or private?\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773215751650}}
