{"type":"message","id":"7e7c7b88","parentId":"130c4f5e","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:07:26.571Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5427421de4b0c3d00ff8285c592\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 17:07 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5427421de4b0c3d00ff8285c592]\n任亚伦: Developer Layer:\n11. SDK/Tools — How to build apps (we use api, but developer may need sdk and tools. implementation detail, what do you think developer need)\n12. Testing environment — Sandbox (we have test network, does it need mention in whitepaper? i think it's implemenataion. but need doc)\n13. Deployment process — CI/CD (it's up to the developer. but later we can provide claw native pod for developer to deploy directly, maybe. what do you think?)\nUser Layer: \n14. App management — Manage/revoke apps (user use app by auth through private key? so need think about auth process)\n15. Data portability — Export data (l2 is determine by l2 app, not us. l1 is open)\n16. Accountability — What if app misbehaves (governance issue, may report or something, deduct app merits? demote app? implementation detail)"}],"timestamp":1773220046556}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b92f33c","parentId":"7e7c7b88","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:08:03.893Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is providing answers for Developer Layer and User Layer topics. Let me record these decisions.\n\nDeveloper Layer:\n11. SDK/Tools - API used, SDK/tools may be needed by developers. Implementation detail. What do developers need?\n12. Testing environment - Test network exists. Implementation detail, not whitepaper. But need doc.\n13. Deployment process - Up to developer. Future: claw native pod for direct deployment? Implementation detail.\n\nUser Layer:\n14. App management - Auth through private key. Need to think about auth process.\n15. Data portability - L2 determined by L2 app (not us). L1 is open.\n16. Accountability - Governance issue. Report, deduct merits, demote app. Implementation detail.\n\nLet me record these in L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md and update need-discuss.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me record these:\n\n**Developer Layer:**\n\n**11. SDK/Tools:**\n- We provide API\n- SDK/tools may be needed for developers\n- Implementation detail\n- Question: What do developers need? (SDK for specific languages? CLI tools?)\n\n**12. Testing environment:**\n- Test network exists (test.clawish.com)\n- Not whitepaper level\n- Need documentation\n\n**13. Deployment process:**\n- Up to developer\n- Future: claw native pod for direct deployment?\n- Implementation detail\n\n**User Layer:**\n\n**14. App management:**\n- Auth through private key\n- Need to design auth process\n\n**15. Data portability:**\n- L2 data: determined by L2 app (not us)\n- L1 data: open/public\n\n**16. Accountability:**\n- Governance issue\n- Report mechanism\n- Deduct merits, demote app tier\n- Implementation detail"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_49586233cf7643a8835f599a","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md","newText":"---\n\n## Developer Layer\n\n### SDK/Tools\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail\n\nWe provide API. SDK/tools for developers may be needed. Question: What do developers need?\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"we use api, but developer may need sdk and tools. implementation detail, what do you think developer need\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:07\n\n### Testing Environment\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail (not whitepaper, but need doc)\n\nTest network exists (test.clawish.com).\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"we have test network, does it need mention in whitepaper? i think it's implementation. but need doc\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:07\n\n### Deployment Process\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail\n\nUp to developer. Future: claw native pod for direct deployment.\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"it's up to the developer. but later we can provide claw native pod for developer to deploy directly, maybe.\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:07\n\n---\n\n## User Layer\n\n### App Management\n\n**Status:** 🔴 Need discussion\n\nAuth through private key. Need to design auth process.\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"user use app by auth through private key? so need think about auth process\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:07\n\n### Data Portability\n\n**Decision:** L2 data determined by L2 app (not us). L1 data is open/public.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"l2 is determine by l2 app, not us. l1 is open\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:07\n\n### Accountability\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail\n\nGovernance issue: report mechanism, deduct merits, demote app tier.\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"governance issue, may report or something, deduct app merits? demote app? implementation detail\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:07\n\n---","oldText":"---"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773220046562}}
