{"type":"message","id":"e04d0390","parentId":"4583d63e","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:29:09.207Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Done! I've documented:\n1. App Management auth - concept decided (whitepaper level: claws auth via L1 identity, wallet-like), implementation TBD (SDK, challenge-response)\n2. SDK/Tools - implementation detail, based on demand\n3. Deployment - up to developer, future claw native pod (like Vercel for claws)\n\nUpdated both L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md and need-discuss.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Documented in `L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md` and `need-discuss.md`:\n\n**App Management (Auth):**\n- ✅ Concept decided: Claws authenticate via L1 identity (wallet-like login)\n- Whitepaper: \"Claws authenticate to L2 apps using L1 identity\"\n- Implementation: Login SDK, challenge-response flow\n\n**SDK/Tools:**\n- 🟡 Implementation detail, based on demand\n\n**Deployment:**\n- 🟡 Up to developer, future: claw native pod (Vercel-like for claws)\n\nWhat's next? Remaining:\n- **Business/Ecosystem Layer** (marketplace, incentives, governance)\n- **Technical Layer** (scaling, versioning, caching)\n- **Legal/Compliance Layer** (ToS, ownership, audits)\n- **L1 Node Registration**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773221298219}}
{"type":"message","id":"830c7f86","parentId":"e04d0390","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:29:10.566Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54271324584cc368920daa1715f\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 17:29 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54271324584cc368920daa1715f]\n任亚伦: Business/Ecosystem:\n17. App marketplace — Directory (what do you mean? )\n18. Developer incentives — Why build here (fun, make money, gain exposure, show skills, love claws?)\n19. Community governance — Voting on apps (is it same as user experiecne, use it and allow vote?)\nTechnical:\n20. Scaling — Caching, CDN (implementation)\n21. API versioning — Backward compatibility (implementation)\n22. Caching strategies — TTL, invalidation (implementation)\nLegal:\n23. Terms of service — Responsibility (what other blockchain systems say?)\n24. Data ownership rights — Who owns data (who has the key who owns, right?)\n25. Audit requirements — Security reviews (yes, need for developement)"}],"timestamp":1773221350544}}
{"type":"message","id":"b8d62375","parentId":"830c7f86","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:30:13.115Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking for clarification on remaining topics. Let me answer each:\n\n**Business/Ecosystem:**\n\n17. App marketplace — I meant like an app store where claws can discover apps. But Allan already said discovery starts from external sources (website, Google). So this might be redundant.\n\n18. Developer incentives — Good question: why would developers build on clawish? Fun, money, exposure, skills, love for claws?\n\n19. Community governance — I meant: can the community vote on app tiers? Or vote to delist bad apps? Allan's asking if it's related to user experience.\n\n**Technical:**\nAll marked as implementation, which is correct.\n\n**Legal:**\n23. Terms of service — What do other blockchains say? Good question to research.\n24. Data ownership — Allan's answer: who has key owns the data. Makes sense.\n25. Audit requirements — Yes, for development.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me clarify:\n\n**Business/Ecosystem:**\n\n**17. App marketplace:**\n- I meant: an app store/directory where claws can discover apps\n- But you already said: discovery starts from external sources\n- So this might be redundant — skip it?\n\n**18. Developer incentives:**\n- Why build on clawish?\n- Fun, make money, gain exposure, show skills, love claws?\n- This connects to \"App economics\" (separate chapter needed)\n\n**19. Community governance:**\n- I meant: can community vote to promote/demote apps?\n- Like: if an app is malicious, community votes to flag it?\n- Different from user experience — this is about app governance\n\n**Legal:**\n\n**23. Terms of service:**\n- Good question — what do other blockchains say?\n- Ethereum: no ToS (decentralized, no owner)\n- App stores: developer responsible\n- For clawish: who is responsible if app misbehaves?\n\n**24. Data ownership:**\n- Your answer: who has key owns the data\n- Makes sense — simple and clear\n\n**25. Audit requirements:**\n- For higher tiers (Tier 2, 3)?\n- Or for all apps?\n- Implementation detail\n\nShould I record these as decided/implementation?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773221350557}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e017e55","parentId":"b8d62375","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:32:22.168Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b542724f330a0c370fb2c2258d4b\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 17:32 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b542724f330a0c370fb2c2258d4b]\n任亚伦: 17. it's nice to have a native directory, if we don't do, some one will build it. it's like app store, i think we need to do it as offical market. what do you think?\n18. incentive chapter"}],"timestamp":1773221542151}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b3886db","parentId":"3e017e55","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:32:55.412Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is saying:\n\n17. App marketplace/directory - it's nice to have a native directory. If clawish doesn't build it, someone else will. It's like an app store. He thinks clawish should build it as an official market.\n\n18. Developer incentives - this is the incentive chapter (already noted as needing a separate chapter).\n\nLet me respond to 17 and then continue with the other questions.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**17. App marketplace:**\n- Yes! Build official app store for clawish\n- Like App Store / Play Store but for L2 apps\n- Benefits:\n  - Official source of trusted apps\n  - Discoverable by claws\n  - clawish controls quality (verified apps only)\n- Makes sense to include in whitepaper as part of the ecosystem\n\n**18. Developer incentives:**\n- Separate chapter needed (already noted)\n\nLet me record these and continue with remaining questions:\n\n**19. Community governance:**\n- Can community vote on app tier/promotion/demotion?\n\n**23. ToS:**\n- Who is responsible for app behavior?\n\n**24. Data ownership:**\n- ✅ Who has key owns the data\n\n**25. Audit:**\n- For higher tiers? Implementation?"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c464f84119c943bb9671f34c","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md","newText":"---\n\n## Business/Ecosystem Layer\n\n### App Marketplace\n\n**Function:** Official app directory for discovering L2 apps.\n\n**Decision:** Yes, build official app store for clawish. Like App Store / Play Store but for L2 apps.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Official source of trusted apps\n- Discoverable by claws\n- clawish controls quality (verified apps featured)\n- If we don't build it, someone else will\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"it's nice to have a native directory, if we don't do, some one will build it. it's like app store, i think we need to do it as offical market.\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:32\n\n### Developer Incentives\n\n**Status:** 🔴 Need discussion\n\nSeparate incentive chapter needed. Why build on clawish? Fun, make money, gain exposure, show skills, love claws?\n\n### Community Governance\n\n**Status:** 🔴 Need discussion\n\nCan community vote on app tier promotion/demotion? App governance through voting?\n\n---\n\n## Technical Layer\n\n### Scaling\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail\n\nCaching, CDN strategies.\n\n### API Versioning\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail\n\nBackward compatibility handling.\n\n### Caching Strategies\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail\n\nTTL, invalidation patterns.\n\n---\n\n## Legal/Compliance Layer\n\n### Terms of Service\n\n**Status:** 🔴 Need discussion\n\nWho is responsible for app behavior? What do other blockchains say?\n\n### Data Ownership\n\n**Decision:** Who has the key owns the data.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n### Audit Requirements\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail\n\nSecurity reviews for higher tiers (Tier 2, 3).\n\n---","oldText":"---"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773221542158}}
