plementation detail\n+609 \n+610 TTL, invalidation patterns.\n+611 \n+612 ---\n+613 \n+614 ## Legal/Compliance Layer\n+615 \n+616 ### Terms of Service\n+617 \n+618 **Status:** 🔴 Need discussion\n+619 \n+620 Who is responsible for app behavior? What do other blockchains say?\n+621 \n+622 ### Data Ownership\n+623 \n+624 **Decision:** Who has the key owns the data.\n+625 \n+626 **Status:** ✅ Decided\n+627 \n+628 **Context & Discussion:**\n+629 > Allan: \"who has the key who owns, right?\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:29\n+630 \n+631 ### Audit Requirements\n+632 \n+633 **Status:** 🟡 Implementation detail\n+634 \n+635 Security reviews for higher tiers (Tier 2, 3).\n+636 \n+637 **Context & Discussion:**\n+638 > Allan: \"yes, need for developement\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:29\n+639 \n+640 ---\n+641 \n 559 ## Related Documents\n 560 \n 561 | Document | Date | Purpose |\n 562 |----------|------|---------|\n     ...","firstChangedLine":559},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773221635169}}
