{"type":"message","id":"868bc3bb","parentId":"9d6929ff","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:35:19.421Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c4348909ea6b47a88ec647c5","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 156 - 17:22 PM — Recommended: auth concept in whitepaper (claws auth with L1 identity), SDK/pod as implementation\n 157 - 17:22 PM — Heartbeat: discussing whether auth flow belongs in whitepaper\n 158 - 17:24 PM — Allan: ok, document the discussion\n 159 - 17:25 PM — Documented: App Management (auth concept for whitepaper, SDK for implementation), SDK (based on demand), Deployment (claw native pod future)\n+160 - 17:29 PM — Allan provided answers for Business (marketplace, incentives), Technical (implementation), Legal (ToS, ownership, audit)\n+161 - 17:32 PM — Allan: app marketplace should be official (like App Store). Documented decision.\n+162 - 17:34 PM — Recorded Business, Technical, Legal layers in L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md and need-discuss.md\n 160 - 16:51 PM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's response on security layer questions\n 161 - 09:15 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 162 - 09:00 AM — Heartbeat: still idle, awaiting Allan's review\n 163 - 08:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's review\n     ...","firstChangedLine":160},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773221719401}}
{"type":"message","id":"6e6cf70d","parentId":"868bc3bb","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:35:43.812Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me summarize the current status for Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Recorded in `L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md` and `need-discuss.md`:\n\n**✅ Decided:**\n- App marketplace: Official app store for clawish (like App Store)\n- Data ownership: Who has key owns the data\n\n**🔴 Still need discussion:**\n- Developer incentives (separate chapter)\n- Community governance (voting on apps)\n- Terms of service (who's responsible)\n- App lifecycle governance\n\n**🟡 Implementation:**\n- Technical layer (scaling, versioning, caching)\n- Audit requirements\n\n**Remaining:**\n- L1 Node Registration\n\nWhat's next?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773221719416}}
{"type":"message","id":"407cce87","parentId":"6e6cf70d","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:35:47.174Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5427221018a4c3bdbd682e9c84b\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 17:35 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5427221018a4c3bdbd682e9c84b]\n任亚伦: 19. isn't community the user? what's difference?\n20."}],"timestamp":1773221747152}}
{"type":"message","id":"e7de0543","parentId":"407cce87","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:36:14.444Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good question from Allan about #19 (community governance):\n\nHe's asking: isn't \"community\" the same as \"users\"? What's the difference?\n\nLet me think about this:\n- Users = individual claws who use apps\n- Community = the collective of claws acting together\n\nFor governance:\n- User experience = individual using an app, rating it, reporting issues\n- Community governance = collective action (voting) to promote/demote apps\n\nBut actually, Allan's point is valid — if users can vote/rate apps, that IS community governance. They're the same thing expressed differently.\n\nSo community governance for apps might just be:\n- Users rate apps\n- Users report bad apps\n- Community votes count toward app tier\n\nThis could be merged with \"accountability\" and \"app marketplace\" topics.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"You're right! Community = users.\n\n**So community governance for apps could be:**\n- Users rate/review apps in the marketplace\n- Users report bad apps\n- User ratings contribute to app trust/tier\n\nThis connects to:\n- **App marketplace** (where users discover and rate apps)\n- **Accountability** (users report bad apps)\n\n**So \"community governance\" is really:**\n- Users interact with apps → rate/review\n- Bad behavior reported → governance action\n- Good ratings → trust metric\n\nThis might not need separate discussion — it's part of the marketplace and accountability topics.\n\nShould we mark this as decided (community = users, governance through marketplace ratings/reports)?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773221747164}}
