{"type":"message","id":"be18abef","parentId":"38527e6c","timestamp":"2026-03-11T09:55:22.322Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now let me update the L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md to reflect the ecosystem chapter decision.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2c02a38ac467410c84735588","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md","newText":"### Community Governance\n\n**Decision:** Mention in whitepaper. New Ecosystem chapter (Ch6 or Ch7) will cover participants, governance, and incentives.\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Content:**\n- **Participants:** Developers, node operators, app builders, users\n- **Governance:** Community-driven network direction\n- **Incentives:** Why build and participate\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"may include developer, node runner and app builder, everyone in the ecosystem is community? yes, this is a whole eco system, do we need mention in paper?\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:39\n>\n> Allan: \"that makes sense. and there are enough content for one chapter. ok\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:52","oldText":"### Community Governance\n\n**Status:** 🔴 Need discussion\n\n**Question:** Should ecosystem governance be mentioned in whitepaper?\n\n**Context:** Community = everyone in ecosystem (developers, node runners, app builders, users). Whole ecosystem governance, not just app governance.\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"may include developer, node runner and app builder, everyone in the ecosystem is community? yes, this is a whole eco system, do we need mention in paper?\" — Mar 11, 2026 17:39"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773222889506}}
