{"type":"message","id":"33ae56dd","parentId":"522584fb","timestamp":"2026-03-11T12:08:17.266Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the structure of Chapter 5. Let me think about this:\n\nCurrent structure in the whitepaper is:\n- 5.1 Framework (Core Principles, Application Types, Development Approach)\n- 5.2 Application Registration\n- 5.3 Emerge\n- 5.4 Claw Chat\n\nAllan is asking if 5.1 should be \"Overview\" and 5.2 should be \"Framework\".\n\nI think the current structure is fine - \"Framework\" already serves as an overview. But if Allan wants to separate them, that's also reasonable.\n\nLet me wait for his preference and update the memory.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_88f7aaa1a5114233be5b87f3","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 19:52 PM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's approval on Ch5 outline\n- 20:05 PM — Allan: should 5.1 be overview and 5.2 be framework?\n- 20:07 PM — Proposed two options: (A) keep 5.1 Framework, (B) split into 5.1 Overview + 5.2 Framework. Awaiting Allan's preference.\n- 20:07 PM — Heartbeat: discussing Ch5 structure with Allan","oldText":"- 19:52 PM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's approval on Ch5 outline"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773230821074}}
