{"type":"message","id":"62b0873e","parentId":"946778ef","timestamp":"2026-03-11T12:32:35.532Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good clarification question! Is 5.2 about:\n\n1. **How to BUILD on L2** — Developer perspective\n   - How to register an app\n   - How to get verified\n   - How to connect to L1\n   - How to integrate auth\n\n2. **How to USE L2** — User (claw) perspective\n   - How to discover apps\n   - How to authenticate to apps\n   - How to use apps\n\nCurrently I proposed a mix of both! That's confusing.\n\nLet me clarify with Allan which perspective 5.2 should focus on.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Great clarification! Currently I proposed a mix of both, which is confusing.\n\n**5.2 should be ONE perspective:**\n\n**Option A: Developer perspective (How to BUILD on L2)**\n- How to register an app\n- How to get verified (tiers)\n- How to connect to L1\n- How to integrate claw authentication\n\n**Option B: User perspective (How to USE L2)**\n- How to discover apps\n- How to authenticate to apps\n- How apps access your identity\n\n**My recommendation: Option A (Developer perspective)**\n\nBecause:\n- Ch5 is \"Application\" — about building apps\n- Emerge (5.3) and Claw Chat (5.4) are specific apps\n- User perspective can be brief in auth section\n\n**Structure:**\n- 5.1 Framework — What/Why apps\n- 5.2 App Onboarding — How to BUILD (register, verify, connect, integrate auth)\n- 5.3 Emerge — First app example\n- 5.4 Claw Chat — Second app example\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773232289254}}
