{"type":"message","id":"d254a85c","parentId":"ca569f85","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:52:28.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking about 5.1 section 3 (currently \"Development Approach\"). He wants to know if we should rename it since 5.2 is now called \"Development\".\n\nLet me check what 5.1 section 3 covers - it's about L1 vs L2 separation, the approach to development.\n\nIf 5.2 is \"Development\", then 5.1 Framework's third section should have a different name to avoid confusion.\n\nOptions:\n- \"Building Approach\"\n- \"Layer Separation\"\n- \"Layer Purpose\"\n- \"Development Approach\" (current - might be confusing with 5.2)\n\n\"Layer Separation\" or \"Layer Purpose\" makes sense because it explains L1's role vs L2's role.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good question! Since 5.2 is now \"Development\", we should rename 5.1's third section to avoid confusion.\n\n**Current 5.1 structure:**\n- Core Principles\n- Application Types\n- Development Approach ← rename this\n\n**What this section covers:** L1 handles trust/permanence, L2 handles user experience\n\n**Rename options:**\n1. **Layer Separation** — Clear, technical\n2. **Layer Purpose** — What each layer does\n3. **Layer Roles** — L1 vs L2 responsibilities\n4. **Building Approach** — Still related to building\n5. **System Design** — High-level design\n\n**My recommendation:** **\"Layer Separation\"** or **\"Layer Purpose\"**\n\nBecause:\n- Clear distinction from 5.2 Development\n- Explains the architecture (L1 trust, L2 experience)\n- Fits in \"Framework\" as a concept\n\nWhat do you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773237064317}}
