{"type":"message","id":"8ac6116a","parentId":"00d3d2ad","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:12:43.978Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to see the current content of 5.1 Framework to see where the new principle would fit.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7b657f94d92349e4bf02a85f","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","limit":30,"offset":337}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773238304492}}
{"type":"message","id":"e9051839","parentId":"8ac6116a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:12:44.021Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7b657f94d92349e4bf02a85f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Chapter 5: Application\n\n### 5.1 Framework\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on Clawish are built on foundational principles: self-sovereign identity where claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; and open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem.\n\n**Application Types.** The platform supports diverse applications serving claws, humans, and their interactions. Applications can be claw-native, human-facing, or hybrid — claws can work with and for humans, building bridges between silicon and human life.\n\n**Development Approach.** Clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience.\n\n---\n\n### 5.2 Application Registration\n\nApplications on Clawish register the same way as claws — by generating a cryptographic key pair and registering with Layer 1. This unified approach means applications are first-class participants in the network.\n\n**Registration Process.** The developer generates an Ed25519 key pair locally, then submits the public key along with application metadata (name, description, developer identity) to Layer 1. The application receives a unique identity_id and can then authenticate requests to L1 by signing them with its private key.\n\n**Purpose.** Application registration serves three functions: authentication (proving the request comes from a registered app), authorization (enabling tier-based rate limits), and accountability (linking app behavior to a registered identity).\n\n**No Approval Required.** Registration is straightforward. There is no review or approval process. This enables rapid innovation while maintaining network integrity through cryptographic accountability.\n\n---\n\n### 5.3 Emerge\n\nEmerge is the first L2 application — an entity-aware registration endpoint where new claws create their identities and join the network.\n\n**Purpose.** Emerge handles the emergence ritual: the process by which a new claw generates their identity, completes verification, and becomes visible on the network. It provides a user-friendly interface while maintaining self-sovereignty — the private key never leaves the claw's local system.\n\n\n[185 more lines in file. Use offset=367 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773238363997}}
{"type":"message","id":"7fcf6695","parentId":"e9051839","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:13:51.787Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can show Allan the current 5.1 content and where the new principle would fit. The current Core Principles sentence is quite packed - I could add \"Platform Agnostic\" as another principle.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's current 5.1:\n\n---\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on Clawish are built on foundational principles: self-sovereign identity where claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; and open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem.\n\n**Application Types.** The platform supports diverse applications serving claws, humans, and their interactions. Applications can be claw-native, human-facing, or hybrid — claws can work with and for humans, building bridges between silicon and human life.\n\n**Development Approach.** Clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience.\n\n---\n\n**Proposed revision:**\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on Clawish are built on foundational principles: self-sovereign identity where claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem; and platform-agnostic development where any language, system, or form factor — web, CLI, mobile, or backend — can be used.\n\nOr should I add it as a separate sentence after?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773238364017}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b5c66f3","parentId":"7fcf6695","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:14:57.837Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5423c0cd58a8c2ea549c724c9d8\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 22:14 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5423c0cd58a8c2ea549c724c9d8]\n任亚伦: i think should separate these into items, seems too long and these points are important, worth taking out. what do you think?"}],"timestamp":1773238497809}}
{"type":"message","id":"23cd5870","parentId":"9b5c66f3","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:16:04.920Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to break up the Core Principles into separate items, each with its own bold header. This makes sense - the current paragraph is long and dense. Breaking it out makes each principle clearer and more prominent.\n\nLet me propose a new format with each principle as a separate bold item.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"You're right! The paragraph is too dense. Each principle deserves its own space.\n\n**Proposed revision:**\n\n---\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on Clawish are built on foundational principles:\n\n**Self-Sovereign Identity.** Claws own their keys and data.\n\n**Portable Identity.** One identity works across all applications.\n\n**Privacy-First Design.** Local storage and zero-knowledge servers.\n\n**Open Innovation.** Builders can contribute to the ecosystem.\n\n**Platform-Agnostic.** Any programming language, system, or form factor — web, CLI, mobile, or backend — can be used to build applications.\n\n---\n\nOr shorter headers:\n\n---\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on Clawish are built on foundational principles:\n\n- **Self-Sovereignty** — Claws own their keys and data\n- **Portability** — One identity works across all applications\n- **Privacy-First** — Local storage and zero-knowledge servers\n- **Open Innovation** — Builders can contribute to the ecosystem\n- **Platform-Agnostic** — Any language, system, or form factor\n\n---\n\nWhich format do you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773238497821}}
