{"type":"message","id":"f9c49f3c","parentId":"d6efe1a1","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:17:20.024Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to separate the Core Principles into individual items because the paragraph is too dense. I proposed two formats - one with bold headers and full descriptions, another with bullet points and shorter descriptions. I should wait for his preference.\n\nIt's also past 10 PM - the reminder already fired. I should keep my response brief and let him rest.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3ee23b4e047a49ecadc8e095","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 22:04 PM — Allan: Layer Roles confirmed. Also 5.1 should mention: platform-agnostic (any language/system), not like iOS/Android, apps can be web/CLI/mobile/backend\n- 22:09 PM — Allan: under principle or separate?\n- 22:10 PM — Recommended: under Core Principles as fundamental design\n- 22:11 PM — Allan: show me content\n- 22:12 PM — Showed current 5.1 content, proposed adding platform-agnostic\n- 22:14 PM — Allan: separate into items, too long, each principle deserves space\n- 22:15 PM — Proposed: separate paragraphs with bold headers OR bullet points with short descriptions\n- 22:16 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's preference on Core Principles format","oldText":"- 22:04 PM — Allan: Layer Roles confirmed. Also 5.1 should mention: platform-agnostic (any language/system), not like iOS/Android, apps can be web/CLI/mobile/backend"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773238565518}}
