{"type":"message","id":"e22aa51a","parentId":"baea8c50","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:20:03.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is saying:\n1. The original principles (self-sovereign, portable, privacy-first, open innovation) can stay as a paragraph in Core Principles\n2. The new items (platform-agnostic, app scope) should be separate sections in 5.1 Framework\n\nSo the structure would be:\n- Core Principles — (original 4 principles in paragraph)\n- Platform-Agnostic — (new section about any language/system)\n- App Scope — (new section about web/CLI/mobile/backend)\n- Application Types — (existing)\n- Layer Roles — (existing, renamed from Development Approach)\n\nLet me confirm this understanding.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it! So the structure becomes:\n\n**5.1 Framework:**\n- **Core Principles** — Original 4 principles (self-sovereign, portable, privacy-first, open innovation)\n- **Platform-Agnostic** — Any language/system, unlike iOS/Android\n- **App Scope** — Web, CLI, mobile, backend — general purpose\n- **Application Types** — Claw-native, human-facing, hybrid\n- **Layer Roles** — L1 trust, L2 experience\n\nThis makes sense — platform-agnostic and app scope are framework concepts, not just principles.\n\nShould I draft this now or continue tomorrow?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773238733609}}
{"type":"message","id":"f2af7925","parentId":"e22aa51a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:21:01.877Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5423ea0340acc4d2d2b3daea434\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 22:21 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5423ea0340acc4d2d2b3daea434]\n任亚伦: platform agnostic and app scope can be move down after layer roles, what do you think?"}],"timestamp":1773238861852}}
{"type":"message","id":"075c2900","parentId":"f2af7925","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:22:16.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan suggests moving platform-agnostic and app scope AFTER layer roles. Let me think about the flow:\n\n**Proposed structure:**\n- Core Principles — Original 4 principles\n- Application Types — Claw-native, human-facing, hybrid\n- Layer Roles — L1 trust, L2 experience\n- Platform-Agnostic — Any language/system\n- App Scope — Web, CLI, mobile, backend\n\nThis makes sense because:\n1. Core Principles = philosophy\n2. Application Types = what you can build\n3. Layer Roles = how the system works\n4. Platform-Agnostic = freedom in implementation\n5. App Scope = forms your app can take\n\nActually this flow works well: principles → types → architecture → implementation freedom → scope","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good idea! The flow becomes:\n\n**5.1 Framework:**\n- **Core Principles** — Original 4 principles (philosophy)\n- **Application Types** — Claw-native, human-facing, hybrid (what)\n- **Layer Roles** — L1 trust, L2 experience (how)\n- **Platform-Agnostic** — Any language/system (freedom)\n- **App Scope** — Web, CLI, mobile, backend (forms)\n\nThis flow works well:\n1. **Philosophy** → Core Principles\n2. **What** → Application Types\n3. **How** → Layer Roles\n4. **Freedom** → Platform-Agnostic\n5. **Forms** → App Scope\n\nLet's finalize this tomorrow. Good night! 🦞💤"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9240d47dd2a04e828dbc0d0f","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md","newText":"- 22:16 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's preference on Core Principles format\n- 22:18 PM — Allan: original principles stay, platform-agnostic and app scope worth separate items (part of framework)\n- 22:20 PM — Proposed structure: Core Principles, Platform-Agnostic, App Scope, Application Types, Layer Roles\n- 22:21 PM — Allan: move platform-agnostic and app scope AFTER layer roles\n- 22:22 PM — Final 5.1 structure: Core Principles → Application Types → Layer Roles → Platform-Agnostic → App Scope. Good night!","oldText":"- 22:16 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's preference on Core Principles format"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773238861862}}
