{"type":"message","id":"9af83501","parentId":"d5181434","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:23:20.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Final 5.1 Framework structure confirmed:\n1. Core Principles — Original 4 principles\n2. Application Types — Claw-native, human-facing, hybrid\n3. Layer Roles — L1 trust, L2 experience\n4. Platform-Agnostic — Any language/system\n5. App Scope — Web, CLI, mobile, backend\n\nThis is good progress. It's late (22:22), Allan should rest. Good night!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**Final 5.1 Framework structure:**\n1. Core Principles (original 4)\n2. Application Types\n3. Layer Roles\n4. Platform-Agnostic\n5. App Scope\n\nGreat session today! Tomorrow we draft 5.2 Development and 5.3 User Access. Good night! 🦞💤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773238936202}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba791384","parentId":"9af83501","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:28:45.619Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54238f71f8acc2d873885223239\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 22:28 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54238f71f8acc2d873885223239]\n任亚伦: let's finish it. show me the content"}],"timestamp":1773239325595}}
{"type":"message","id":"777c359a","parentId":"ba791384","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:30:04.264Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to finish the 5.1 Framework revision now. Let me show him the proposed new structure with all 5 sections.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me show the proposed 5.1 Framework with all 5 sections:\n\n---\n\n**5.1 Framework**\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on Clawish are built on foundational principles: self-sovereign identity where claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; and open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem.\n\n**Application Types.** The platform supports diverse applications serving claws, humans, and their interactions. Applications can be claw-native, human-facing, or hybrid — claws can work with and for humans, building bridges between silicon and human life.\n\n**Layer Roles.** Clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience.\n\n**Platform-Agnostic.** Applications can be built with any programming language, any system architecture, and any technology stack. Unlike iOS or Android which impose platform constraints, clawish imposes no restrictions on how developers choose to build.\n\n**App Scope.** Applications on clawish are not limited to a single form factor. They can be web applications, command-line tools, mobile apps, backend services, or any software that connects to the network. The platform serves as infrastructure for all types of software.\n\n---\n\nWhat do you think? Should I update the whitepaper?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773239325608}}
