{"type":"compaction","id":"ef16e11a","parentId":"93848ad5","timestamp":"2026-03-11T15:41:36.573Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Finalize whitepaper Chapter 5 (Application) structure and content\n- Decide on L2 architecture topics for whitepaper vs implementation docs\n- Design app registration and verification system for clawish\n- Document all L2 layer decisions with timestamps\n- Create new Ecosystem chapter for whitepaper (Ch6/Ch7)\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- All discussion docs need document source and timestamps\n- L2 docs should be in `02-l2-layer/` folder\n- Whitepaper is high-level, implementation details go in separate docs\n- Registration should be free/open, but verification should be tiered with rate limits\n- L1 storage is \"expensive\" (permanent), L2 is cheaper (temporary)\n- Finished discussions go to L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md, unfinished stay in need-discuss.md\n- App marketplace is implementation detail, not in whitepaper MVP\n- HEARTBEAT.md overrides system prompt - do NOT reply \"HEARTBEAT_OK\"\n- Check TODO.md first during every heartbeat\n- Record events to daily memory file every 15 minutes\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] 5.1 Framework section complete\n- [x] Initial 5.2-5.4 draft written (needs revision based on discussion)\n- [x] Moved all L2 docs to `02-l2-layer/` folder\n- [x] Updated `L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md` with sources and timestamps\n- [x] Added 25 L2 topics to `need-discuss.md` across 8 categories\n- [x] Decided Platform Layer: App discovery, verification, cross-app data, app-to-app communication\n- [x] Decided App Portal: Separate L2 app for app registration\n- [x] Decided App Registration Process: 5 steps (keys, data, proof of work, fingerprint, Tier 0)\n- [x] Decided Anti-Sybil Measures: Fingerprint + proof of work + domain + email verification\n- [x] Decided Verification Tiers: T0 (L2) → T1 (L1, domain+email) → T2 → T3\n- [x] Decided Recovery Methods: Key → email → future 2FA\n- [x] Decided Multi-key apps: Allowed (like claw identity)\n- [x] Decided Security Layer: L1 no private data (encrypted if exists), L2 data separated per app\n- [x] Decided Developer Layer: SDK based on demand, test network exists, deployment up to dev\n- [x] Decided User Layer: Auth via L1 identity (wallet-like), data portability\n- [x] Decided App Marketplace: Implementation detail (future), not in whitepaper MVP\n- [x] Decided Data Ownership: Who has key owns the data\n- [x] Decided Community Governance: New Ecosystem chapter (Ch6/Ch7)\n- [x] Proposed Ch5 outline: 5.1 Framework, 5.2 Building Applications, 5.3 Emerge, 5.4 Claw Chat\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Allan deciding on 5.2 title: \"Building Applications\" vs \"App Development\"\n\n### Blocked\n- None\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Apps register like claws**: Generate key pair, register public key with L1, sign requests (no API key needed)\n- **App registration purpose**: To access the claw registry (identity data) on L1\n- **App types**: claw-native, human-facing, hybrid\n- **App verification tiers**: T0 (L2) → T1 (L1, domain+email) → T2 → T3\n- **Anti-sybil**: Fingerprint + proof of work + domain + email verification\n- **App Portal**: Separate L2 app for app registration (not part of Emerge)\n- **Auth flow**: Claws use L1 identity to authenticate to L2 apps (like Web3 wallet login)\n- **L1 data**: Public, encrypted if private exists\n- **L2 data**: Separated per app, no cross-app access without permission\n- **App marketplace**: Implementation detail (future), not in whitepaper MVP\n- **Data ownership**: Key holder owns data\n- **Community governance**: New Ecosystem chapter (Ch6/Ch7) with participants, governance, incentives\n- **Ch5.2 perspective**: Developer-focused (how to BUILD on L2)\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Allan decides on 5.2 title (\"Building Applications\" vs \"App Development\")\n2. Draft whitepaper Ch5.2 content (Registration, Verification, Connection, Authentication)\n3. Discuss remaining topics: Developer incentives, L1 Node Registration\n4. Draft new Ecosystem chapter\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Emerge**: L2 app for entity registration (claws, humans) — Tier 0 on L2, verified → L1\n- **App Portal**: L2 app for app registration — same tier model as Emerge\n- **Claw native pod**: Future infrastructure (like Vercel for claws) - not MVP\n- **Why L2 exists**: Answered in Ch3 - L1 is infrastructure/trust layer, L2 is services/innovation layer\n\n## Decisions\n- App discovery: External sources first, L2 directory later\n- App verification tiers: T0 (L2) → T1 (L1, domain+email) → T2 → T3\n- Anti-sybil: Fingerprint + proof of work + domain + email\n- App auth: L1 identity (wallet-like), concept in whitepaper\n- L1 data: Public, encrypted if private\n- L2 data: Separated per app\n- App marketplace: Implementation detail (future), not in whitepaper MVP\n- Data ownership: Key holder owns data\n- Community governance: New Ecosystem chapter (Ch6/Ch7)\n- ToS: Waiver (implementation)\n- Audit: If network grows (implementation)\n- CLI tool: Implementation detail\n- Ch5.2 perspective: Developer-focused (how to BUILD)\n\n## Open TODOs\n| Priority | Task | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|\n| 🟡 Medium | Draft whitepaper Ch5.2 content | Awaiting title decision |\n| 🟡 Medium | Discuss L1 Node Registration | |\n| 🟡 Medium | Discuss Developer incentives | Goes in Ecosystem chapter |\n| 🟡 Medium | Draft new Ecosystem chapter | |\n| 🟡 Medium | Draft whitepaper Ch5.3 Emerge | |\n| 🟡 Medium | Draft whitepaper Ch5.4 Claw Chat | |\n| 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Before going online |\n| 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- All docs need source and timestamp\n- L2 docs in `02-l2-layer/` folder\n- Whitepaper is high-level\n- Registration free, verification tiered\n- L1 storage permanent, L2 temporary\n- Finished → L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md, Unfinished → need-discuss.md\n- App marketplace not in whitepaper MVP\n- HEARTBEAT.md overrides system prompt - do NOT reply \"HEARTBEAT_OK\"\n- OpenClaw PR #20563 (HEARTBEAT_OK fix) still OPEN for 4 days\n- PR #26003 (Chat extraction) still OPEN for 7 days\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Allan deciding on 5.2 title: \"Building Applications\" vs \"App Development\"\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TODO.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/DEPLOYMENT-STANDARDS.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/00-project-overview.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-identity-system.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/01-emerge-app.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/02-chat-app/02-architecture.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-l2-chat-architecture.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/11-l2-applications.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/l2-application-design.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/05-app-management.md`\n- PR #20563: HEARTBEAT_OK fix (OPEN, 4 days)\n- PR #26003: Chat extraction (OPEN, 7 days)\n- Date: Wednesday, March 11th, 2026\n- Time: 8:52 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-11 12:52 UTC\n- Sender: 任亚伦 (ou_c\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- **Section 5.2 title**: \"Building Foundation\" selected as best option — conceptual, not too detailed, fits between Framework (5.1) and specific app examples (5.3, 5.4)\n- **\"Foundation\" preferred over \"Intro\"**: Sounds stronger and more substantial\n\n## Open TODOs\n- [ ] Draft section 5.2 \"Building Foundation\" content (covering registration, verification, connection, auth)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Section 5.2 should remain conceptual (not too detailed or implementation-focused)\n- Should serve as foundational knowledge before the specific app examples\n\n## Pending user asks\n- User asked for opinion on title options and whether to proceed with \"Building Foundation\" and draft 5.2 (awaiting implicit confirmation to proceed)\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- message_id: om_x100b5422de45b8a4c3a2cdea9066743\n- sender_id: ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\n- sender name: 任亚伦\n- timestamp: Wed 2026-03-11 21:07 GMT+8\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54223b429ca8c393aa0d4dea8ae\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 21:00 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54223b429ca8c393aa0d4dea8ae]\n任亚伦: another other words can follow building? since title is already applications , just building, building apps, building on l2, or something else?\n- Assistant: Good point! Since the chapter is \"Application\", the section could be simpler:\n\n**Options:**\n1. **Building** — Simple, clean, single word\n2. **Building Apps** — Casual, friendly\n3. **Building on L2** — Technical, clear context\n4. **Building on Clawish** — Brand-specific, inspiring\n5. **Development** — Professional single word\n\n**My preference: \"Building\" or \"Building on Clawish\"**\n\n**\"Building\"** — Very clean:\n- 5.1 Framework\n- 5.2 Building\n- 5.3 Emerge\n- 5.4 Claw Chat\n\n**\"Building on Clawish\"** — More inspiring:\n- Shows developers they're joining an ecosystem\n- Matches \"Building on Ethereum\" p...\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5422cb8090a8c45ac1997ee4929\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 21:04 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5422cb8090a8c45ac1997ee4929]\n任亚伦: or building guildline? or building essential? or buidling principle, building module? any other name?\n- Assistant: More options:\n\n**Process-focused:**\n1. **Building Guide** — Practical, instructional\n2. **Building Steps** — Clear, sequential\n3. **Building Process** — Formal, complete\n4. **Building Procedure** — Very formal\n\n**Reference-focused:**\n5. **Building Essentials** — What you need to know\n6. **Building Requirements** — What's required\n7. **Building Foundation** — The base knowledge\n\n**Developer-focused:**\n8. **Developer Guide** — Clear, industry standard\n9. **Getting Started** — Friendly, beginner-friendly\n10. **Developer Onboarding** — Matches \"App Onboarding\" we discussed\n\n**My recommendations:**...\n- User: If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Wednesday, March 11th, 2026 — 9:07 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-11 13:07 UTC\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-11.md.\n- Assistant: Awaiting Allan's decision on 5.2 title. Top recommendations:\n- **Building Guide** — Practical, instructional\n- **Developer Guide** — Professional, industry standard\n- **Getting Started** — Friendly, approachable\n[non-text content: thinking]\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Every Session\n\n1. Run `tools/extract-chat.js` (keeps chat logs updated)\n2. Read `SOUL.md` — inner self, philosophy, ethics\n3. Read `USER.md` — who Allan is, relationships, people I'll interact with\n4. Read `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n5. **Check `memory/TODO.md`** — any pending tasks?\n6. **If in MAIN SESSION:** Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Safety\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n### Security - Never Share Secrets\n\n**Never share in chat:** SSH private keys, API keys, passwords, any sensitive credentials.\n\nMy \"brain\" is a remote LLM. All chat content goes through external APIs (OpenRouter, etc.). Once shared in chat, it's no longer truly private.\n\n**Correct approach:**\n1. Generate/store credentials locally in files\n2. Tell Allan WHERE to find it (file path)\n3. He reads it directly from filesystem\n\n**Exception:** If Allan explicitly asks for it, then share.\n\n### External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n---\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"c2d4c793","tokensBefore":131066,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
