n process and verification system\n- 14:25 PM — Proposed App Portal registration: (1) Generate keys, (2) Submit to L2 with metadata, (3) Tier 0 assignment\n- 14:28 PM — Proposed verification system: T0→T1 (developer verified OR usage OR vouch), T1→T2 (track record + audit), T2→T3 (long history + formal audit + governance)\n- 14:30 PM — Asked 3 questions: developer verification required? trial period? tier slashing?\n- 14:36 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's feedback on App Portal registration/verification design\n- 14:51 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting Allan's feedback\n- 15:01 PM — Allan: registration process fine, but need website/domain (IP changes), also need signature for system\n- 15:03 PM — Proposed: website URL required, domain verification, key ownership proof (sign challenge)\n- 15:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's confirmation on updated registration process\n- 15:08 PM — Allan: domain verification should be Tier 1 (not optional), also need system signature (browser, IP) to avoid spam\n- 15:10 PM — Allan: system fingerprint for Tier 0 too, avoid massive registration\n- 15:11 PM — Allan asked: is that what sybil attack is?\n- 15:12 PM — Explained sybil attack: one entity creating many fake identities\n- 15:13 PM — Allan: also need math calculation at registration to increase sybil attack cost\n- 15:15 PM — Recorded full App Portal registration process in L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md: (1) Generate keys, (2) Submit data, (3) Proof of work, (4) System fingerprint, (5) Tier 0 assignment\n- 15:15 PM — Recorded verification tiers: T0 (L2, fingerprint), T1 (L1, domain verified), T2 (usage), T3 (audit + governance)\n- 15:19 PM — Allan: contact verify needed for Tier 1 (email), for revert or lost key\n- 15:20 PM — Updated Tier 1: domain ownership + email verification\n- 15:21 PM — Heartbeat: App Portal registration/verification recorded, awaiting next topic\n- 15:24 PM — Allan: domain + email required. Key can change info. Lost both → future: mnemonic, 2FA\n- 15:26 PM — Added recovery methods to docs\n- 15:26 PM — Allan: registration, verify, recovery all discussed. Anything missing?\n- 15:28 PM — Listed: deprecation, tier demotion, updates, multiple devs, transfer, rate limits\n- 15:30 PM — Allan answered: (1) leave on L1 if shutdown, (2) governance rules later, (3) key updates profile, (5) transfer key freely, (6) implementation detail\n- 15:32 PM — Clarified #4: can an app have multiple owners? Proposed: single key owner, team can use multi-sig externally\n- 15:36 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's response on multiple owners question\n- 15:40 PM — Allan: multi-key allowed (like claw identity), equal vs multi-sig = implementation detail. All questions are implementation-related, record in docs\n- 15:41 PM — Updated L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md with multi-key decision and all other topics\n- 15:51 PM — Heartbeat: App Portal design complete, awaiting next topic from Allan\n- 15:51 PM — Allan: Tier 2-3 details later. Now other questions: Operations (lifecycle, economics, monitoring) and Security (permissions, consent, privacy)\n- 15:55 PM — Answered: (5) governance for bad apps, (6) incentive chapter needed, (7) monitoring what? implementation detail\n- 15:58 PM — Asked clarifications: (8) can apps query anything? (9) claw consent for app access? (10) app data vs claw data?\n- 16:06 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's clarification on security layer questions\n- 16:21 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting Allan's response on security layer (permissions, consent, privacy)\n- 16:36 PM — Heartbeat: idle, awaiting Allan's response\n- 16:55 PM — Allan answered: (5) need discuss, (6) need chapter, (7) implementation, (8) L1 no private data or encrypted, (9) L1 public, L2 data separated, (10) L1 is public\n- 16:58 PM — Recorded Operations Layer and Security Layer decisions in L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md\n- 16:59 PM — Allan: finished talk goes to discussion file, unfinished stays in need-discuss\n- 17:00 PM — Updated need-discuss.md: Platform Layer all decided, Security 