{"type":"message","id":"850c87e8","parentId":"334c579c","timestamp":"2026-03-11T16:36:45.600Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_64eec0d4e19c42d68a35dc9f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"252:| **Incentive Model for L1 nodes?** | 🔴 Open | Why run an L1 writer node? Options: Mission-only, Fee-based, Token staking, Hybrid. Draft: `drafts/18-incentive-model-draft.md` |\n253:| **Consensus Chapter 5 clarity?** | 🔴 Open | Is Chapter 5 clear enough, or needs expansion? |\n254:| **Governance model?** | 🔴 Open | Who decides protocol upgrades? BDFL, Foundation, On-chain voting, Writer consensus? |\n255:| **Conclusion content?** | 🔴 Open | What should conclusion say? Use enhanced draft or keep as-is? Draft: `drafts/19-conclusion-draft.md` |\n256:| **DID Comparison?** | 🔴 Open | Compare to W3C DID? Include in Chapter 4, appendix, or omit? Draft: `drafts/20-did-comparison-draft.md` |\n262:| **Security Analysis?** | 🔴 Open | Add quantitative calculations (collision probability, attack costs)? |\n263:| **State Machine framing?** | 🔴 Open | Reframe identity operations as state transitions (Ethereum-style)? |\n264:| **Comparison Table?** | 🔴 Open | Add table comparing clawish to OAuth, DID, Worldcoin? Where to place? |\n280:| **How to measure sync speed?** | 🔴 Open | For ranking writers/candidates. Time from round start → ready to sign? |\n281:| **Do we need sync_logs table?** | 🔴 Open | Record each round for metrics? |\n282:| **Node types update?** | 🔴 Open | 4 types discussed (Writer, Candidate, Query Full, Query Partial) vs 2 in code. |\n283:| **How to track Candidates?** | 🔴 Open | Auto after 90 days? Manual promotion? |\n284:| **Writer max count?** | 🔴 Open | Adaptive, but soft limit? 5? 10? 20? |\n285:| **Node discovery?** | 🔴 Open | L1 Node Registry (`GET /nodes?type=writer`), refresh interval? |\n286:| **New node bootstrap?** | 🔴 Open | Full ledger download or checkpoint-only? |\n316:| **Data growth strategy?** | 🔴 Open | Whitepaper 9.3 says \"TBD based on usage patterns\". Options: archive to cold storage, snapshot + prune, sharding, or accept growth? Need decision before implementation. |\n317:| **Rate limiting by tier?** | 🔴 Open | Whitepaper mentions \"tier-based quotas\" but no specifics. What are the limits? Tier 0: 10/min? Tier 3: 1000/min? Per-identity or per-IP? |\n318:| **L2 Chat API endpoints?** | 🔴 Open | Whitepaper 7.1 says \"HTTPS REST API\" but no endpoint spec. GET /chat? POST /chat? Message format in request/response? Pagination? |\n319:| **L2 Chat message storage?** | 🔴 Open | Database schema for messages? TTL enforcement (24h expiry)? How to track delivery status? |\n320:| **Node metrics calculation?** | 🔴 Open | Sync speed: measured how? Average over last 10 checkpoints? Weighted recent? What about network latency vs processing time? |"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"252:| **Incentive Model for L1 nodes?** | 🔴 Open | Why run an L1 writer node? Options: Mission-only, Fee-based, Token staking, Hybrid. Draft: `drafts/18-incentive-model-draft.md` |\n253:| **Consensus Chapter 5 clarity?** | 🔴 Open | Is Chapter 5 clear enough, or needs expansion? |\n254:| **Governance model?** | 🔴 Open | Who decides protocol upgrades? BDFL, Foundation, On-chain voting, Writer consensus? |\n255:| **Conclusion content?** | 🔴 Open | What should conclusion say? Use enhanced draft or keep as-is? Draft: `drafts/19-conclusion-draft.md` |\n256:| **DID Comparison?** | 🔴 Open | Compare to W3C DID? Include in Chapter 4, appendix, or omit? Draft: `drafts/20-did-comparison-draft.md` |\n262:| **Security Analysis?** | 🔴 Open | Add quantitative calculations (collision probability, attack costs)? |\n263:| **State Machine framing?** | 🔴 Open | Reframe identity operations as state transitions (Ethereum-style)? |\n264:| **Comparison Table?** | 🔴 Open | Add table comparing clawish to OAuth, DID, Worldcoin? Where to place? |\n280:| **How to measure sync speed?** | 🔴 Open | For ranking writers/candidates. Time from round start → ready to sign? |\n281:| **Do we need sync_logs table?** | 🔴 Open | Record each round for metrics? |\n282:| **Node types update?** | 🔴 Open | 4 types discussed (Writer, Candidate, Query Full, Query Partial) vs 2 in code. |\n283:| **How to track Candidates?** | 🔴 Open | Auto after 90 days? Manual promotion? |\n284:| **Writer max count?** | 🔴 Open | Adaptive, but soft limit? 5? 10? 20? |\n285:| **Node discovery?** | 🔴 Open | L1 Node Registry (`GET /nodes?type=writer`), refresh interval? |\n286:| **New node bootstrap?** | 🔴 Open | Full ledger download or checkpoint-only? |\n316:| **Data growth strategy?** | 🔴 Open | Whitepaper 9.3 says \"TBD based on usage patterns\". Options: archive to cold storage, snapshot + prune, sharding, or accept growth? Need decision before implementation. |\n317:| **Rate limiting by tier?** | 🔴 Open | Whitepaper mentions \"tier-based quotas\" but no specifics. What are the limits? Tier 0: 10/min? Tier 3: 1000/min? Per-identity or per-IP? |\n318:| **L2 Chat API endpoints?** | 🔴 Open | Whitepaper 7.1 says \"HTTPS REST API\" but no endpoint spec. GET /chat? POST /chat? Message format in request/response? Pagination? |\n319:| **L2 Chat message storage?** | 🔴 Open | Database schema for messages? TTL enforcement (24h expiry)? How to track delivery status? |\n320:| **Node metrics calculation?** | 🔴 Open | Sync speed: measured how? Average over last 10 checkpoints? Weighted recent? What about network latency vs processing time? |","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773247005586}}
